wp-content/uploads/2014/07/slide-81.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(803,1,'2015-11-06 09:27:23','2015-11-06 09:27:23','','slide-3','','inherit','open','closed','','slide-3-2','','','2015-11-06 09:27:23','2015-11-06 09:27:23','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/slide-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(804,1,'2015-11-06 09:28:51','2015-11-06 09:28:51','','slide-6','','inherit','open','closed','','slide-6-3','','','2015-11-06 09:28:51','2015-11-06 09:28:51','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/slide-61.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(851,1,'2015-11-12 12:03:12','2015-11-12 12:03:12','','itunes-ratings','','inherit','open','closed','','itunes-ratings','','','2015-11-12 12:03:12','2015-11-12 12:03:12','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/itunes-ratings.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(888,1,'2016-02-28 10:44:20','2016-02-28 10:44:20','<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>what HIIT is and what it does for you</li>\n	<li>why HIIT works for every fitness level</li>\n	<li>how pro-athletes use HIIT to train effectively</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nHigh-intensity interval training describes any workout that alternates between intense bursts of activity and fixed periods of less-intense activity or even complete rest. HIIT can be a workout regimen or a jogging/sprint interval option. This type of training gets and keeps your heart rate up. HIIT-workouts makes resistance training a lot tougher while increasing your fitness overall. What makes HIIT so effective is the so called afterburn effect. It is the number one reason why HIIT is the best alternative to burn fat in less time.  After you finished your HIIT, you will burn more fat and calories than with regular aerobic and steady-state workouts during your regeneration and rest phase. Hence, HIIT is very important to get fit and athletic in the beginning, but also to get lean and ripped if you are an advanced athlete.\n\nThere is two forms of utilizing HIIT. On one hand there are HIIT-workouts which most of the time can be done at home and consists of full body exercises. On the other hand there are HIIT-runs which are timed intervals for running. At Ykings you can replace the one with the other to be in control of your training. Just don\'t skip it.\n\nA good HIIT workout starts with a well-rounded warmup. The high intensity intervals should be performed at near maximum effort and the recovery intervals in a comfortable effort. A real advantage of HIIT is that it is fully adjustable to a person\'s needs. Independent of fitness level you could always make it challenging for the particular athlete. Let\'s have a look at the 30/30 HIIT-run regimen with four full rounds for a total of 12 minutes. In its original layout you would do a light jogging pace for 30 seconds and the go for 30 seconds sprinting, however if you are not quite there yet, walk instead of jogging and jog instead of sprinting. This is how you could easily adjust HIIT to your own purpose and fitness level. No excuses, get it done.\n<ul>\n	<li>Minutes 1-4 (Warm-Up) - Jog at a comfortable level</li>\n	<li>Minute 5 (Workout Interval 1) Jog/Walk 30 seconds</li>\n	<li>Sprint/Jog 30 seconds at maximum effort</li>\n	<li>Minute 6 (Workout Interval 2) Jog/Walk 30 seconds</li>\n	<li>Sprint/Jog 30 seconds at maximum effort</li>\n	<li>Minute 7 (Workout Interval 3) Jog/Walk 30 seconds</li>\n	<li>Sprint/Jog 30 seconds at maximum effort</li>\n	<li>Minute 8 (Workout Interval 4) Jog/Walk 30 seconds</li>\n	<li>Sprint/Jog 30 seconds at maximum effort</li>\n	<li>Minutes 9-12 (Cool-Down) - Jog at a comfortable level</li>\n</ul>\nMany Pro-athletes and celebrities use HIIT as their preferred option to cut weight in no time. Diligent work ethics doing the HIIT is what makes pro athletes a pro athlete. To be more exact, pros keep their maximum speed at all times during the high intense interval. This means that it is advantageous on a scale of 1-10 (where is 5 standard jogging and 10 is maximum speed) to switch to a speed of 8 or 9 to allow you to perform the interval with the best effort. Additionally some athletes might like the idea of doing the sprints at a slight incline up a hill. The optimal HIIT is achieved when you feel a slight burning in your body after the workout. Last but not least you have to pay attention to the underground and safety. We recommend joint-gentle surfaces like tartan tracks and paths in the forest. Caution on rainy days and when paths are covered with leaves, snow and pebbles.\n\nWhat about you? Do you like HIIT? Any tips to share? Let us know.\n\nPS: In one of our next articles, we will cover HIIT even in more depth and list all the benefits of HIIT.\n\n<strong><em>Ykings is a full body training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves. One of our principles at Ykings is that we believe HIIT gets the best out of you in the shortest time. The efficiency of HIIT is the reason why you will find HIIT-runs as well as HIIT-strength workouts in our workout portfolio. Depending on your personal goals and fitness level, HIIT will play a crucial factor to get you either in shape and learn all bodyweight training skills or elevate your arsenal as you reach new levels. </em></strong>\n\n#StriveForProgress\n\n&nbsp;','How to utilize High Intensity Interval Training (HIIT)','','publish','open','open','','all-about-high-intensity-interval-training-hiit','','','2016-02-28 10:44:20','2016-02-28 10:44:20','',0,'http://stage.ykings.com/?p=888',0,'post','',0),(890,1,'2016-01-05 14:16:30','2016-01-05 14:16:30','<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>what the benefits from HIIT are</li>\n	<li>why HIIT is popular</li>\n	<li>pre-HIIT - what “base fitness level” is</li>\n</ul>\nHIIT training can easily be modified for people of all fitness levels and special conditions, including overweight and diabetes. HIIT workouts can be performed on cycling, swimming, aqua training, jogging or sprinting, just to name a few.\n\nIn the last 2 years, fitness enthusiasts have put their heart rate monitors, essential for cardio workout on the shelves, with the advance of HIIT. Whilst the proven theory for cardio workout has been “more is more” for sustained fat loss, HIIT on the contrary, consists of short bouts of all-out efforts alternating with stretches of recovery. Shorter work out sessions combined with rest for crazy fat loss? Yes. You read that right. However, one will actually be working much harder than the guy on the nearby treadmill. No surprise that many reports have strongly indicated undeniable results from HIIT. HIIT tend to burn more calories than traditional workouts, especially afterward. The post-exercise period is called “EPOC” - Excess Post-exercise Oxygen Consumption. This is generally about a 2-hour period after training where the body is restoring itself to pre-exercise levels, and thus using more energy. Because of the vigorous nature of HIIT workouts, the EPOC generally tends to be higher, adding about 6 to 15% more calories to the overall workout energy expenditure.\n\nHIIT training has been shown to improve:\n<ul>\n	<li>metabolism</li>\n	<li>blood pressure</li>\n	<li>cardiovascular health</li>\n	<li>insulin sensitivity (helps exercising muscles more readily use glucose to make energy)</li>\n	<li>cholesterol profiles</li>\n	<li>abdominal fat and body weight while maintaining muscle mass.</li>\n</ul>\nPrior to beginning HIIT training, you are recommended to establish a foundational level of fitness – a “base fitness level”, which can be consistent aerobic training (3 to 5 times a week for 20 to 60 min per session) for several weeks. This helps promote muscular adaptations - improving oxygen transport to the muscles. Establishing appropriate exercise form and muscle strength are important before engaging in regular HIIT to reduce the risk of musculoskeletal injury.\n\nRegardless of age, gender and fitness level, one of the keys to optimal participation of HIIT training is to modify the intensity of the work interval to a preferred challenging level. This is where your Virtual Coach plays a crucial role in finding your own optimal training intensities as opposed to you simply trying to keep up with the Peers.','HIIT - The benefits of HIGH INTENSITY INTERVAL TRAINING','','draft','open','open','','hiit-the-benefits-of-high-intensity-interval-training','','','2016-01-05 14:16:30','2016-01-05 14:16:30','',0,'http://stage.ykings.com/?p=890',0,'post','',0),(900,1,'2015-12-29 16:01:09','2015-12-29 16:01:09','','001','Outdoor portrait of female athlete while resting on the stairway. She is holding sports bottle and also has mobile phone attached to her arm with white headphones around her neck.','inherit','open','closed','','001','','','2015-12-29 16:01:09','2015-12-29 16:01:09','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/001.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(901,1,'2015-12-29 16:01:20','2015-12-29 16:01:20','','002','Young female fitness athlete stretching her leg on the bridge after jogging. ','inherit','open','closed','','002','','','2015-12-29 16:01:20','2015-12-29 16:01:20','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/002.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(902,1,'2015-12-29 16:01:37','2015-12-29 16:01:37','','003','','inherit','open','closed','','003','','','2015-12-29 16:01:37','2015-12-29 16:01:37','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/003.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(903,1,'2015-12-29 16:01:51','2015-12-29 16:01:51','','004','','inherit','open','closed','','004','','','2015-12-29 16:01:51','2015-12-29 16:01:51','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/004.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(904,1,'2015-12-29 16:02:02','2015-12-29 16:02:02','','005','','inherit','open','closed','','005','','','2015-12-29 16:02:02','2015-12-29 16:02:02','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/005.jpg',0,'attachmen