ew/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/File-Jan-08-8-21-56-AM.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(999,1,'2016-01-08 07:40:28','2016-01-08 07:40:28','','File Jan 08, 8 22 26 AM','','inherit','open','closed','','file-jan-08-8-22-26-am','','','2016-01-08 07:40:28','2016-01-08 07:40:28','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/File-Jan-08-8-22-26-AM.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1000,1,'2016-01-08 07:40:36','2016-01-08 07:40:36','','File Jan 08, 8 38 30 AM','','inherit','open','closed','','file-jan-08-8-38-30-am','','','2016-01-08 07:40:36','2016-01-08 07:40:36','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/File-Jan-08-8-38-30-AM-e1452498025406.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1001,1,'2016-01-11 07:09:51','2016-01-11 07:09:51','','sarah FA1','','inherit','open','closed','','sarah-fa1','','','2016-01-11 07:09:51','2016-01-11 07:09:51','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/sarah-FA1-e1455825738680.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1003,1,'2016-01-11 08:17:01','2016-01-11 08:17:01','<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>where calisthenics and street workout fit in the movement culture</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>what you have to focus on entering the movement arena</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>how your mind and strength helps to control your body</strong></li>\n</ul>\nMany modern athletes forgot about the importance of movement. These days the importance shifts back and you can witness it already in various sports. Take a look at MMA fighters, many of them have movement coaches who make them faster, more powerful and overall better fighters. Urban gymnastics also known as street workout or calisthenics is very popular and people get back to learn elite static gymnastic skills from scratch. The movement culture is embedded in yoga, capoeira but also in calisthenics. For those of you who do calisthenics professionally, a broader focus on the movement culture can help tremendously to come up with new skills and moves for your freestyle sessions. The movement culture is the new paradigm shift in fitness. Vivid proof of that is the popularity of sports such as functional training, crossfit and yoga.\n\n<a href=\"http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/4866138077_f101833817_o.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1004\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-1004\" src=\"http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/4866138077_f101833817_o-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"A group of men and women practice capoeira on the beach in Dili, Timor-Leste, preparing for upcoming events such as International Youth Day, 12 August.\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" /></a>\n\nMovement is liquid and two elements that get you started are quality work on your flexibility and mobility. These two will help to gradually develop your strength and skill level. In today\'s civilized world flexibility and mobility have become a core problem. Just think about how many hours a day you spent on just sitting? So if you want to spent some more time taking control of and creating awareness over your body, you should give your health a higher priority. The simple rule is to invest a good portion of time in your health; otherwise you will spend the same amount of time later on your illness.\n\nBuilding a strong body requires a clear and dedicated mindset. Your mind builds your strength which leads to your goals and perform those moves. Before evolving to a master of body control you will have to get more flexibile and find your balance. All the power of a body centered lifestyle comes from your core.  If you are up for it, you are already in the right place. Learn, evolve, master!\n\nYkings helps you to get a foot into the world of movement. The progression formula secures your gradual development to achieve better body awareness and epic body skills. Join a community of like-minded and start your own journey.\n\nPS: In one of our next articles we will cover in which way you will not need any rest days.','How to enter the world of movement','','publish','open','open','','how-to-enter-the-world-of-movement','','','2016-01-11 08:17:01','2016-01-11 08:17:01','',0,'http://stage.ykings.com/?p=1003',0,'post','',2),(1004,1,'2016-01-11 08:13:24','2016-01-11 08:13:24','','Capoeira Practice on Dili Beach','A group of men and women practice capoeira on the beach in Dili, Timor-Leste, preparing for upcoming events such as International Youth Day, 12 August.','inherit','open','closed','','capoeira-practice-on-dili-beach','','','2016-01-11 08:13:24','2016-01-11 08:13:24','',1003,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/4866138077_f101833817_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1005,1,'2016-01-11 08:15:27','2016-01-11 08:15:27','','15327097294_733b2c4c48_k','','inherit','open','closed','','15327097294_733b2c4c48_k','','','2016-01-11 08:15:27','2016-01-11 08:15:27','',1003,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/15327097294_733b2c4c48_k.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1009,1,'2016-01-11 08:33:46','2016-01-11 08:33:46','','11501332465_3650b10bfe_k','','inherit','open','closed','','11501332465_3650b10bfe_k','','','2016-01-11 08:33:46','2016-01-11 08:33:46','',1003,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/11501332465_3650b10bfe_k-e1452501282738.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1010,1,'2016-01-11 08:41:47','2016-01-11 08:41:47','What to do?\n• 2/3 cup cooked oatmeal, prepared with water\n• 1 scoop of protein powder or ½ cup of cottage cheese\n• ½ cup of fresh or frozen berries\n• 1-1/2 Tbsp. chopped walnuts\n• Splash (1/4 cup) of skim, almond, rice or soy milk\n\nBigger meal?:\n• Increase oatmeal to 1 cup\n• Increase protein powder to 1-1/2 scoops or 1 cup of cottage cheese\n\nbon appetit\n:-)','Oatmeal – Breakfast','','publish','open','open','','oatmeal-breakfast','','','2016-01-11 08:41:47','2016-01-11 08:41:47','',0,'http://stage.ykings.com/?p=1010',0,'post','',0),(1011,1,'2016-01-11 08:41:03','2016-01-11 08:41:03','','blueberries-531209_1920','','inherit','open','closed','','blueberries-531209_1920','','','2016-01-11 08:41:03','2016-01-11 08:41:03','',1010,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/blueberries-531209_1920.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1016,1,'2016-01-11 10:13:00','2016-01-11 10:13:00','<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>what impact your peers have on you</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>why you have to associate yourself with the right people</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>why a dedicated workout group gives you opportunities\n</strong></li>\n</ul>\nBeing in the game of change and new interests, your peer group profoundly impacts your progress. Your peers are a mirror of yourself and influence whom you socialize with, who become members of your network and they are the filter by which you consider all your decisions.\n\nIf you want to achieve a specific goal in your life, get around those people who already achieved your goal. It sounds simple, however most people don’t put enough effort and persistence into choosing a peer group. Truth is, many get out in the working world, and the people around you become part of your peer group just because you happen to see them a lot. They just fall into whatever peer group happens to be the most convenient. Go out there and actively look for people with the same interest. While this is somewhat natural, you miss an opportunity when you don’t proactively choose at least some portion of your peer group. In the fitness world this is your workout group or your social connection to a bunch of like-minded people.\n\n<a href=\"http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/023.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-922\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-922\" src=\"http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/023-683x1024.jpg\" alt=\"023\" width=\"406\" height=\"609\" /></a>\n\nThe motivation, the advice and the experience you can share with your workout group is priceless. If you haven’t devoted energy to building your relationships, consider doing now. If you are not sure how to find people around you interested the same thing, you have to find your community. Wanna get started? What\'s holding you back?\n\nConnect and learn from the pros. Our community grows together. #WeGrowTogether. Ykings brings a community of dedicated people together. Look out for daily advice from Team Ykings and our featured athletes. Strive for progress my friend.\n\nPS: In of our next posts we will cover the benefits of doing HIIT.','The power of a dedicated workout group','','publish','open','open','','the-power-of-a-dedicated-workout-group','','','2016-01-11 10:13:00','2016-01-11 10:13:00','',0,'http://stage.ykings.com/?p=1016',0,'post','',0),(1027,1,'2016-01-12 08:06:28','2016-01-12 08:06:28','','YKINGS1-Black-72dpi','','inherit','open','closed','','ykings1-black-72dpi','','','2016-01-12 08:06:28','2016-01-12 08:06:28','',616,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/YKINGS1-Black-72dpi-e1452586022859.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1032,1,'2016-01-12 08:19:36','2016-01-12 08:19:36','','art-alley-run','','inherit','open','closed','','art-alley-run','','','2016-01-12 08:19:36','2016-01-12 08:19:36','',634,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/art-alley-run.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1047,1,'2016-01-14 09:02:21','2016-01-14 09:02:21','','030','','inherit','open','closed','','030-2','','','2016-01-14 09:02:21','2016-01-14 09:02:21','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/030.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1049,1,'2016-01-18 10:24:15','2016-01-18 10:24:15','','logo','','inherit','open','closed','','logo','','','2016-01-18 10:24:15','2016-01-18 10:24:15','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/logo-1.png',1,'attachment','image/png',0),(1050,1,'2016-01-18 10:38:24','2016-01-18 10:38:24','','logo02','','inherit','open','closed','','logo02','','','2016-01-18 10:38:24','2016-01-18 10:38:24','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/logo02.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1051,1,'2016-01-18 10:41:34','2016-01-18 10:41:34','','logo','','inherit','open','closed','','logo-3','','','2016-01-18 10:41:34','2016-01-18 10:41:34','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1053,1,'2016-01-19 11:26:09','2016-01-19 11:26:09','','art-alley-run','','inherit','open','closed','','art-alley-run-2','','','2016-01-19 11:26:09','2016-01-19 11:26:09','',890,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/art-alley-run-e1453202814486.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1058,1,'2016-01-19 12:03:34','2016-01-19 12:03:34','<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>how to decrease the potential of shoulder injury </strong></li>\n	<li><strong>what packing your shoulders means</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>the benefits of focusing on perfect form</strong></li>\n</ul>\nYour shoulders are one of the most mobile joints in your body. The high mobility factor increases also the potential for injury. To prevent injury effectively you have to know about isolating your shoulders. There are four positions you should keep in mind during your workouts for certain exercises. The terminologies for the four positions are protraction and retraction as well as depression and elevation. We covered the terms in more detail on our website, here. But to make it short protraction and retraction is known as moving your scapulae outwards and towards each other, while depression and elevation is known as moving your scapulae down and up.\n\nIn Ykings workouts you will come across these terms quite frequently and when we refer to packing your shoulders it means that you should depress your scapulae or pushing your shoulders down. Some people will hear the term packing the shoulder and immediately think of immobilizing the shoulder. This is not what we mean. Packing the shoulder means motor control over a range of motion that isolates specific injury prone movements. So, make use of depression in exercises that include dipping or static holds such as the L-Sit.\n\nAnother important routine to further increase your mobility are exercises such as the shoulder dislocate. These mobility exercises are often overlooked, but at Ykings we have integrated several exercises in each warmup to ensure you focus on shoulder health, strength and mobility. Most of people who work out have strength and mobility in specific ranges of motion. Motions and movements in the range of the front body to overhead such as pushups, handstands, rows, pullups are well developed, however what about your backside? Starting out with working out at the bar and rings more, you might belong to the high percentage of people who lack behind the body to overhead mobility. So integrate different mobility enhancing exercises in your routine and you will develop and evolve faster.\n\nWhat do you do for more mobility in your joints? What are your best mobility exercises for shoulders, hips and legs? Please leave a comment and subscribe to our mailing list to get more awesome information.\n\nPS: In one of our next articles we will cover the benefits of stretching after each workout.\n\nYkings is a smartphone application that focuses on your overall mobility and flexibility to perform epic moves. In our personalized workout plans Ykings diligently helps you on every workout day to focus effectively to increase your range of motion.\n\n&nbsp;','What packing your shoulders actually means','','publish','open','open','','what-packing-your-shoulders-actually-means','','','2016-01-19 12:03:34','2016-01-19 12:03:34','',0,'http://ykings.com/?p=1058',0,'post','',1),(1059,1,'2016-01-19 12:00:11','2016-01-19 12:00:11','','16948306508_f98259be7c_k','','inherit','open','closed','','16948306508_f98259be7c_k','','','2016-01-19 12:00:11','2016-01-19 12:00:11','',1058,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/16948306508_f98259be7c_k-e1453204824388.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1064,1,'2016-01-25 14:38:18','2016-01-25 14:38:18','After reading this article you will know\n<ul>\n	<li>why stretching should be a workout priority</li>\n	<li>the benefits of stretching especially when learning calisthenics</li>\n	<li>that stretching is a mind and muscle balancing tool</li>\n</ul>\nStretching is probably the most underrated part of a complete workout. Although stretching is the most natural and automatic action of people when waking up and after hours of inactivity, it is still skipped regularly by a lot of athletes. Regular stretching routines are far less emphasized by many, but they are just as important as your workouts. The topic is overall somewhat controversial and study results are split on various subtopics. We recommend giving a good stretching routine a higher priority in your workouts, especially when you get started to do more advanced functional training and tap into the world of calisthenics and gymnastics.\n\nStarting to learn the moves and skills of gymnastics and street workout, a certain degree of flexibility and range of motion is required. Our experience has shown that those athletes we trained that dedicated more time and effort in stretching improved faster with their progressions while also developing a good posture. An increase in flexibility is accompanied by improved balance, coordination, fluidity and speed. These elements need to be well developed if you want to move up the ladder with calisthenics skills. While it is still widely debated as to whether or not stretching can help prevent injury, it has been proven to help increase blood flow to the muscles, thereby possibly reducing muscle soreness and speeding up the recovery process. Calisthenics is the sport of progression and strength. Strength workouts consume a lot of your energy, so there are high incentives to overcome that energy depletion in a healthy way. In other words…..stretch!\n\nEach of us is prone to fall out of balance in our own way. But as with most things in life we need balance to simply feel better. What has that to do with stretching? While strength exercises will shorten your muscles, stretching your muscles will make them longer and more flexible. Understand stretching as the perfect balancing tool to your hard training. The same holds true for your mindset. Stretching in its most sophisticated form is yoga and you can’t deny the point that a good stretching routine will allow your body to recharge while your mind is calm. Make use of the mental break and listen to your body. Finally use a good stretching routine on rest days if you like want to benefit your recovery. Put in perspective, stretching helps your mind and body to have a more balanced training effect; getting you even faster to your goals.\n\nWhich priority have you given stretching up to now? Ever considered to incorporate them in your workout regularly? Tell us more about your experiences and leave a comment to join the discussion with us.\n\nPS: In our next article on this topic, we will cover how and when to incorporate stretching in your workouts.\n\n<strong><em>Ykings is a full body training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves from competitive gymnastics to calisthenics. Our in-app coaching function and progression formula integrates not only your skill level in the workouts, it also includes dynamic warmup sessions and good structured stretching routines. Join the Ykings family and get guided step by step with perfect tailored workout plans.</em></strong>','How stretching influences your training - stretching essentials part 1','','publish','open','open','','how-stretching-influences-your-training-stretching-essentials-part-1','','','2016-01-25 14:38:18','2016-01-25 14:38:18','',0,'http://ykings.com/?p=1064',0,'post','',0),(1065,1,'2016-01-25 14:32:28','2016-01-25 14:32:28','','IMG_2387','','inherit','open','closed','','img_2387','','','2016-01-25 14:32:28','2016-01-25 14:32:28','',1064,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/IMG_2387-e1453732427210.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1068,1,'2016-02-01 12:38:56','2016-02-01 12:38:56','After reading this article you will know\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>why rings are a mandatory tool to implement</li>\r\n	<li>the non-training benefits of rings</li>\r\n	<li>how to get started with rings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nGymnastics rings are showing up in more gyms than ever before. Functional training is becoming very popular and you can observe the shift most probably in your current gym. The good thing, you can also easily setup rings at home yourself and there are a lot of reasons to do it. Many people mistakenly believe these wooden implements are only useful for athletes who use them in competition, like gymnasts or CrossFit athletes. However in reality, anyone can use the rings and benefit from them tremendously, because they help simultaneously build strength, stability, and coordination like no other apparatus. What you may not know about rings, though, is how effectively they build more than just upper body strength, muscular size and definition. Exercises are more valuable on rings than on pull up bars. Why? Compare a muscle up on a pullup bar and a muscle up on rings. Rings cover most of the exercises that you can do with a pullup bar, but it gives you also <strong><u>additional challenges</u></strong> in balancing and control. Overall that <strong><u>benefits your body awareness and control</u></strong>. So if you have room for a little investment or just thinking about getting a pullup bar, keep your eyes and mind also open for gymnastics rings.\r\n\r\nProfessional gymnasts show the whole spectrum of movements that can be performed with rings. They also show how much <strong><u>strength and concentration</u></strong> rings require to master. One of the great advantages of rings is that they <strong><u>require little space</u></strong> and are highly portable. Just compare packing either rings or a pullup bar in your luggage. We’ll bet you, you will choose the rings. Furthermore rings can <strong><u>be mounted quite flexibly</u></strong> and <strong><u>adjusted in height as easily as in width</u></strong>. This enables you to <strong><u>cover the most prestigious bodyweight exercises</u></strong> with one single apparatus anywhere you go.\r\n\r\nIf you are already a working out in the field of calisthenics you most probably have come across rings. For all those considering putting rings into their workout regimen, keep in mind that as with your progress with elite skills and moves, rings will require your patience and dedication. Accept rings as a challenge and push through. To get started to getting accustomed with rings start slowly transferring your usual routine to rings. Another way to acclimate with this new training style is by following this <strong><u>simple routine</u></strong>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/02/File-Feb-28-11-39-13-AM-e1456655976415.jpeg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1077\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1077\" src=\"http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/02/File-Feb-28-11-39-13-AM-e1456655976415.jpeg\" alt=\"File Feb 01, 1 35 20 PM\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Top position holds – 3 rounds of 5-10 seconds\r\n</strong>Don’t forget to pack your shoulder when at the rings. Quality form at the rings is mandatory, so please take also a look at our “<a href=\"http://ykings.com/?p=1058\">what it actually means to pack your shoulders</a>” article for more information.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Ring Dips – 3 rounds of 3-5 reps</strong>\r\nFocus on good movement and explore the variety of muscles you can train by just positioning your upper body differently.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Australian Pullups – 3 rounds of 3-5 reps\r\n</strong>Australian Pullups are your go to move for effectively building the strength for pullups and chin-ups.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease warmup with a shoulder or joint dynamic stretching routine to prevent you from injury. Master your body control on rings first and after you feel a bit more comfortable using the rings, incorporate rings exercises into your regular training as you see a fit.\r\n\r\nHow have you used rings in your past? Ever considered to incorporate them in your workouts? What are your experiences while using rings? Has it changed your physique? Please leave a comment and join the discussion with us.\r\n\r\nPS: In one of our next articles, we will cover what you can learn from your failures and how it can benefit your life overall.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Ykings is a full body training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves. All exercises we provide are bodyweight exercises only and most of them can be done either with bars or rings. We are only days away before our Smartphone App will hit the stores. To be notified firsthand, subscribe to our mailing list. Get also informed about new articles like this to benefit your workouts. Learn, evolve, master.</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>#WeGrowTogether #StriveForProgress</em></strong>','Why you should implement rings in your workout routine','','publish','open','open','','why-you-should-implement-rings-in-your-workout-routine','','','2016-06-10 14:07:03','2016-06-10 14:07:03','',0,'http://ykings.com/?p=1068',0,'post','',0),(1069,1,'2016-02-01 11:54:26','2016-02-01 11:54:26','','22212109302_298a30f252_o','','inherit','open','closed','','22212109302_298a30f252_o-2','','','2016-02-01 11:54:26','2016-02-01 11:54:26','',1068,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/22212109302_298a30f252_o-e1454327679681.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1077,1,'2016-02-01 12:37:18','2016-02-01 12:37:18','','File Feb 01, 1 35 20 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','file-feb-01-1-35-20-pm','','','2016-02-01 12:37:18','2016-02-01 12:37:18','',1068,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/File-Feb-01-1-35-20-PM-e1454330251994.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1081,1,'2016-02-08 07:21:34','2016-02-08 07:21:34','After reading this article you will know\n<ul>\n	<li>what mental strength is all about</li>\n	<li>how to develop your mental strength</li>\n	<li>how to start a new mental thought process</li>\n</ul>\nMental strength is the ability to create <u>healthy habits</u> to consistently perform toward the upper range of your potential and talent regardless of environmental circumstances. Mentally strong people have clear visions and know how to <u>manage their emotions, thoughts, and behaviors</u> in ways that set them up for success in life as well as in sports. Mental strength influences your motivation to win, endurance to be tough and your healthy state of mind in sports and in life. To develop your mental strength you have to <u>challenge your current beliefs</u> and <u>open up for new ideas</u>. Think about the following concepts and make them work for you, to enjoy a new way of thinking.\n\n<strong>Be positive</strong>- life isn’t always easy and fair, however “When the going gets tough, the tough get going”. A good way to stay positive is to have your goals always in the back of your mind. Anytime you catch yourself slacking, questioning your motivation, or feeling like you want to quit, repeat your personal goals and tell yourself what you are doing this for. Learn to see negativity as a waste of time. Give it no room and crush it anytime it starts to come back.\n\n<strong>Be in control</strong> - stop complaining and feeling sorry for you. Either change it or leave it. Recognize that most of the time you are in control of the situation. All it takes is your attitude. Is failure a win or a devastating loss? The day you see failure as a reason to try again and push harder, you have learned a big lesson. Use failure as an opportunity to grow and improve. Stay in the game and develop the will to keep trying until you get it right.\n\n<strong>Be change</strong> – get out of your comfort zone. Most people are afraid of change. They love to stay in security and in their comfort zone. Understand that change is inevitable and believe in your abilities to adapt. The magic happens outside your comfort zone. So get out there and take on the challenge.\n\n<strong>Be focused</strong> - live for the present and plan for the future. Accept responsibility of your behavior and learn from past mistakes. Think about the most efficient way to tackle a problem and once you find it, stick to it. Eliminate non-sense and guide your attention to the important tasks.\n\n<strong>Be patient</strong> – develop a growth mindset and enjoy the little things. Apply your skills and time to the best of your ability and understand that real change takes time. Admit your shortcoming and continually strive to improve. Moreover focus to celebrate small wins and progress, knowing that you are continuing to improve if you be patient with yourself. #StriveForProgress.\n\nIf you master these thinking patterns you will be able to visualize and achieve your goals. It will show in every new workout week and on each training day. Moreover you will have developed a mental toughness to endure and persevere, a mindset that keeps you going when others give up. Get into a mode of being done with the workout mentally. If you can see it, you can do it.\n\nHave your workouts been a torture? How have you overcome the struggle? Is a little bit of anxiety before each workout healthy? Tell us more about your experiences and leave a comment to join the discussion with us.\n\n<strong><em>Ykings is a full body training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves of competitive gymnastics and calisthenics. Our in-app coaching function and progression formula integrates not only your skill level in the workouts; it connects you also to a like-minded community. Stay positive and motivated with the Ykings family and get guided step by step with perfect tailored workout plans.</em></strong>','The importance of mental strength in sports &amp; how to build it','','publish','open','open','','the-importance-of-mental-strength-in-sports-how-to-build-it','','','2016-02-08 07:21:34','2016-02-08 07:21:34','',0,'http://ykings.com/?p=1081',0,'post','',2),(1104,1,'2016-02-08 07:17:18','2016-02-08 07:17:18','','male-719549_960_720','','inherit','open','closed','','male-719549_960_720','','','2016-02-08 07:17:18','2016-02-08 07:17:18','',1081,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/male-719549_960_720-e1454915854781.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1112,1,'2016-02-10 14:19:45','2016-02-10 14:19:45','','Lower abs workout','Fit woman raising her straight legs hanging on gym bar','inherit','open','closed','','lower-abs-workout','','','2016-02-10 14:19:45','2016-02-10 14:19:45','',620,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/iStock_000051423662_Large-e1455113998137.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1118,1,'2016-02-18 13:56:35','2016-02-18 13:56:35','','IMG-20151110-WA0006','','inherit','open','closed','','img-20151110-wa0006','','','2016-02-18 13:56:35','2016-02-18 13:56:35','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/IMG-20151110-WA0006-e1455803824565.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1119,1,'2016-02-18 13:56:38','2016-02-18 13:56:38','','IMG-20151110-WA0009','','inherit','open','closed','','img-20151110-wa0009','','','2016-02-18 13:56:38','2016-02-18 13:56:38','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/IMG-20151110-WA0009-e1455804849836.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1120,1,'2016-02-18 13:56:40','2016-02-18 13:56:40','','IMG-20151112-WA0006','','inherit','open','closed','','img-20151112-wa0006','','','2016-02-18 13:56:40','2016-02-18 13:56:40','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/IMG-20151112-WA0006-e1455803919747.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1122,1,'2016-02-18 15:03:09','2016-02-18 15:03:09','','FullSizeRender','Power Competition @barwarz Berlin +24kg pullups','inherit','open','closed','','fullsizerender','','','2016-02-18 15:03:09','2016-02-18 15:03:09','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FullSizeRender.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1123,1,'2016-02-18 15:03:13','2016-02-18 15:03:13','','FullSizeRender2','','inherit','open','closed','','fullsizerender2','','','2016-02-18 15:03:13','2016-02-18 15:03:13','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FullSizeRender2-e1455898399176.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1124,1,'2016-02-18 15:03:39','2016-02-18 15:03:39','','IMG_3954','Bruce Lee\'s favourite abs exercise - the dragon flag','inherit','open','closed','','img_3954','','','2016-02-18 15:03:39','2016-02-18 15:03:39','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/IMG_3954-e1455807835740.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1126,1,'2016-02-18 16:29:09','2016-02-18 16:29:09','','001','','inherit','open','closed','','001-2','','','2016-02-18 16:29:09','2016-02-18 16:29:09','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/001-e1455812997628.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1127,1,'2016-02-18 16:29:18','2016-02-18 16:29:18','','002','','inherit','open','closed','','002-2','','','2016-02-18 16:29:18','2016-02-18 16:29:18','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/002-e1455812985550.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1128,1,'2016-02-18 16:29:25','2016-02-18 16:29:25','','6','','inherit','open','closed','','6-2','','','2016-02-18 16:29:25','2016-02-18 16:29:25','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/6-e1455814186456.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1131,1,'2016-02-19 16:13:51','2016-02-19 16:13:51','','FullSizeRender2','','inherit','open','closed','','fullsizerender2-2','','','2016-02-19 16:13:51','2016-02-19 16:13:51','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FullSizeRender2-1-e1455898453336.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1132,1,'2016-02-19 16:21:10','2016-02-19 16:21:10','','IMG_4232','','inherit','open','closed','','img_4232','','','2016-02-19 16:21:10','2016-02-19 16:21:10','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/IMG_4232.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1133,1,'2016-02-21 12:34:18','2016-02-21 12:34:18','After reading this article you will know\n<ul>\n	<li>why learning skills is a matter of decision making</li>\n	<li>three approaches to make time when learning skills</li>\n	<li>why you need a good structure before utilizing your time</li>\n</ul>\nWe get often asked how somebody can make time to learn a specific skill when one has a family and a full time job. The first thing to understand is that working out is a decision, so is learning. In the case of skills and movement training, it is a deliberate decision to 1) learn more things in a structured way and 2) strive for personal goals. The rest is a matter of scheduling, finding or making time to work out.\n\nLet’s say you have your goals and you are ready to re-organize your lifestyle towards training. How could you start to think about making time for workouts? We want to introduce you today into three scheduling strategies that can help you in this process 1) post-workout effort 2) double dipping and 3) dedicated skills training.\n\n<u>Approach #1 – Post workout effort</u>\n\nThe most useful strategy is to do some fundamentals and basics every time you work out. If you engage in some extra work every day the numbers sum up significantly over time. Imagine putting an extra 10 minutes every time you work out. Assuming you do three workouts per week that’s 1,560 minutes or roughly 26 hours a year. As you are physically limited to do a couple hours of straight strength training you have to think about putting in extra minutes here and there. Spending an extra 26 hours on your body awareness, mobility or flexibility over the course of the year is well spent. So don’t just finish the workout but also put some extra time afterwards in the things that matter to you. Embrace the little things on the way to bigger goals. Regarding developing your skills, a structured process to address your training in the right manner such as the progression formula will improve your body effectively. Therefore the post workout effort is a powerful tool you should implement if you are serious about your skills in the long term.\n\n<u>Approach #2 – Double - dipping</u>\n\nWe like the idea of learning new skills, trying new moves, engage in new exercises while working on your conditioning and endurance. What is the point of just getting fitter if you could add a real purpose to your training using the same time slot for both? Make your time slot a win-win. Double dipping is not really a strategy but shows the usefulness of the Ykings training concept. Again a structured approach and the discipline to execute is the key to success. You will be surprised how many people are just overwhelmed with the options calisthenics related sports have to offer and get dragged away by it – not making the process they could make. Hence a good structure and an upright focus on your training are the first things to manage. Double-dipping won’t work when you try to work efficiently on the wrong things. What we call double –dipping is the approach of learning a new skill while you work out. Integrate a good portion of your learning time into your workout time slots and you will see that a deliberate effort will help you to evolve your skill set and learn new skills in a much faster pace. Get two things done in a single time slot.\n\n<u>Approach #3 – Dedicated skills training</u>\n\nThe third approach is to cancel some of your other commitments and deliberately devote time to learning. Clear your mind, clear your agenda and think about this as an investment of time in a better future you. As in business, if you invest you need to get good value out of it. Same applies in your training, because you don’t have the time to learn inefficiently from anyone less than the best and with full dedication and focus. Invest some of your valuable time to get the same learning done in substantially less time just by pure dedication and focus. You are in control. Implement a new habit in your life, e.g. do a warmup session and dedicated skills training every Saturday morning before breakfast or add a 20 minute time slot every Thursday after your workout. Schedule it in your calendar and devote the time. You can’t lose, it is for you anyways. Just remember, what doesn’t get scheduled doesn’t get done.\n\nHave more ideas on how to make time for training? Let us know, leave a comment.\n\n<strong><em>Ykings is a full body training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves from disciplines such as competitive gymnastics &amp; calisthenics. Get involved in the training concept that integrate not only your skill level in your workouts but structures your training so that you can evolve and progress while getting in shape. Join the Ykings family and get guided step by step with perfect tailored workout plans.</em></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','The simple rules of making time to learn specific skills','','publish','open','open','','the-simple-rules-of-making-time-to-learn-specific-skills','','','2016-02-21 12:34:18','2016-02-21 12:34:18','',0,'http://ykings.com/?p=1133',0,'post','',0),(1134,1,'2016-02-21 12:30:33','2016-02-21 12:30:33','','File Feb 21, 1 13 50 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','file-feb-21-1-13-50-pm','','','2016-02-21 12:30:33','2016-02-21 12:30:33','',1133,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/File-Feb-21-1-13-50-PM-e1456057847385.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1140,1,'2016-02-28 10:39:23','2016-02-28 10:39:23','','File Feb 28, 11 39 13 AM','','inherit','open','closed','','file-feb-28-11-39-13-am','','','2016-02-28 10:39:23','2016-02-28 10:39:23','',888,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/File-Feb-28-11-39-13-AM-e1456655976415.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1152,1,'2016-03-16 09:40:33','2016-03-16 09:40:33','[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text][ultimate-faqs][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','FAQs','','publish','closed','closed','','faq','','','2016-09-05 07:01:21','2016-09-05 07:01:21','',0,'http://ykings.com/?page_id=1152',0,'page','',0),(1162,1,'2016-03-16 09:51:04','2016-03-16 09:51:04','&nbsp;\n<table class=\"table-striped\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th></th>\n<th>Free Version</th>\n<th>Pro Version</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Unlimited prototypes and pages</td>\n<td>YES</td>\n<td>YES</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Interactive Widgets for web</td>\n<td>NO</td>\n<td>NO</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Basic Interaction Links</td>\n<td>YES</td>\n<td>NO</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;','Free Vs Pro','','private','closed','closed','','free-vs-pro','','','2016-03-16 09:51:04','2016-03-16 09:51:04','',0,'http://ykings.com/?page_id=1162',0,'page','',0),(1181,1,'2016-03-22 20:43:53','2016-03-22 20:43:53','<em>After reading this article you will know</em>\n<ul>\n	<li><em>why workout programs are like diets</em></li>\n	<li><em>what most workout programs are lacking</em></li>\n	<li><em>why you should engage in a workout concept for long-term success</em></li>\n</ul>\nA workout program is a pre-defined regimen of sport exercises that holds a claim of achieving a fitness goal in a specific amount of time. Many workout programs get people the wanted results but as many are also not able to keep the results for long. In this article we want to turn our attention to the problem with workout programs and which alternatives you should consider choosing the right option for you.\n\nIf you have ever finished a workout program, then you most certainly came across the feeling of either pure joy or asking yourself what you should do next. Your options are simple, either keep doing the current workout program or find a more suitable alternative. While the first option could get boring over time, the other is a painful job of research. How to stay in shape is the remaining question.\n\nLook for alternatives that are sustainable and require your consistent effort. Don’t fall for workout programs which enjoy the same pattern like diets. Diets and workout programs often don’t generate the wished long term benefits. Your body just doesn’t respond so well to short changes of what has been different for your whole life. Change is a process over time and a constant effort to make it a habit. You as a person will have to make time for the training and your body will need time to adjust to it. Most people expect great results in a short period of time and fall for workout programs that get you fit, but don’t have anything else to offer and don’t teach you how to stay in shape. The follow up is what most programs are lacking. After the workout, is before the workout.\n\nTo make things easier, we recommend taking a look at workout concepts which give you long, mid and short term goals and a variety of different training stimuli. Only working through a workout program once will not do the trick. A workout concept on the other hand is characterized by individuality. A good workout concept should be able to personalize your training, regardless of fitness level and contain multiple goals in several fields such as agility, strength, mobility, skills, movement and so on. Understand a workout concept as a process of constant personal improvement. If you can either combine it in a beneficial way with your favorite sport or embed it in your life you will never look back.\n\nHow did you feel after you finished a whole x-weeks workout program? Have you achieved your goals? Leave a comment and let us know.\n\n<strong><em>Ykings is progressive training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves. Learn gradually with the well-rounded progression formula and evolve to a new you. Master challenging exercises from gymnastics and bodyweight training</em></strong>\n\n<strong><em>#WeGrowTogether #StriveForProgress</em></strong>','The reasons to engage rather with a workout concept than a workout program','','publish','open','open','','the-reasons-to-engage-rather-with-a-workout-concept-than-a-workout-program','','','2016-03-22 20:43:53','2016-03-22 20:43:53','',0,'http://ykings.com/?p=1181',0,'post','',2),(1182,1,'2016-03-22 20:42:09','2016-03-22 20:42:09','','Working-out','Young athlete working-out in an outdoor gym','inherit','open','closed','','working-out','','','2016-03-22 20:42:09','2016-03-22 20:42:09','',1181,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/iStock_000063683831_Large-e1458679342975.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1194,1,'2016-04-06 12:54:44','2016-04-06 12:54:44','<strong>Workout Guidelines</strong>\n\n<u>Repetitions &amp; quality form</u>\n\nAt Ykings we are not competing against time, so don’t rush it. Take considerable time to perform each repetition with quality form. Make sure you do each movement slowly and controlled. The slower and controlled you can do one repetition the stronger you will get. Watch the video tutorials for the correct range of motion and continuously work on your form. Work through our pro tips and get a spotter to assist you when trying new moves.\n\n<u>Rest days</u>\n\nRest days are your time to grow. We recommend taking sufficient time between workout days to rest your muscles and regenerate. If you feel muscle soreness then rest and rather do a good stretching or HIIT run session the next day. The better you are rested, the faster you will progress. Engage in the Ykings journey in a healthy fashion to enjoy all benefits in the long-term.\n\n<u>Breaks</u>\n\nYkings workouts &amp; exercises are demanding. Please take breaks when you need them to regain power and your breath. Aim for lesser and shorter breaks as you progress to plateau your strength and endurance. Challenge yourself to grow mentally and physically with us. Be advised to pay attention to your body signals, don’t play through pain. Make sure you read our health and safety guidelines to be safe.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><u>Health / Safety</u></strong>\n\n<strong>Some of our exercises include dynamic components and complex movements. With the complexity of routines, the risk of potential injury increases. Injuries most commonly occur in the ankles, feet, lower back, knees, wrists, and hands, often from overuse or simple stress. Injuries are rarely severe, but if left untreated they can lead to chronic pain and bone fractures. Therefore be well-rested, warmed up and always work out with quality form.</strong>\n\n<strong>If you notice symptoms or serious pain it is required to see your doctor and follow instructions for treatment and recovery. Take body signals that go beyond muscle soreness as an absolute serious warning signal!</strong>\n\n<strong>Your health and safety are our main priority and it should be yours too. Please follow proper training guidelines like in our video tutorials, use safe equipment, and work on complex skills with care. Strive for progress, be consistent and don’t risk an injury.</strong>\n\n<strong><u>Please inform yourself about cases that require the consultation of a professional. If in doubt to whether start or continue Ykings workouts please go and seek medical advice.</u></strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Your Workout Plan</strong>\n\n<u>Warmup &amp; Stretching</u>\n\nWarmups are an essential part of any Ykings workout session. Start each workout session with a good warmup routine that mobilizes your joints and gets your blood flowing. A good warmup will also support you to improve your flexibility and mobility. Warm up muscles with light aerobic exercise, such as jumping jacks, squat jumps or running in place, before beginning training or any new activities.\n\nStretching is important to enable your body to new movement and mobility patterns. Ykings recommends closing each workout session with a strict stretching regimen to shorten your rest period, avoid injury and develop a beneficial post-workout habit.\n\n<u>Fundamentals</u>\n\nFundamentals are a substantial pre-workout routine to build your muscle memory on specific moves, get you flexible and prepare your muscles for the upcoming tasks. Fundamentals have changing routines considering your personal goals and are the optimal preparation to have a great workout.\n\n<u>Skills &amp; progressions</u>\n\nRevisit the skills area from time to time and activate progressions that you want to have integrated in your workout weeks. Each activated progression will increase the workout variety of your training and bring essential parts of each skill together. You will know when to move on to the next progression, just listen to your body. The rule of thumb is to progress every four to five weeks, assuming you workout at least three times a week. The fastest progress is achieved with consistent quality work. However, be well rested and don’t get hurt.\n\n<u>Exercise types</u>\n\nYkings includes a high variety of exercises which are separated in three types.\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Standard exercises</strong>. Achieve the rep count as laid out for these exercises. Split them up in multiple sets early on, but challenge yourself over time performing them in a single attempt.</li>\n	<li><strong>Static holds exercises</strong>. Exercises with a static hold icon will challenge your endurance &amp; strength. Try to get and endure the static holds with a minimum of pauses. Aim for the full static hold in total seconds as you progress.</li>\n	<li><strong>Endurance exercises</strong>. These exercises have a countdown timer. In contrast to static hold exercises these exercises don’t need much time to get into the hold position and start immediately after you start the exercise. Attempt to endure the exercise without breaks until the time is up.</li>\n</ol>\n<u>Workout types</u>\n\nYour workout weeks consist of several workout types such as HIIT-strength workouts, pure strength workouts, single exercises and HIIT runs. Diligently working through those workouts will optimize the efficacy of your training towards your personal goals.\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Strength workouts</strong> - Use strength workouts to work on your form and your strength. Don’t rush while you exercise, however try to minimize your breaks between two exercises. Perform each repetition slowly and controlled for maximum results.</li>\n	<li><strong>HIIT-strength workouts</strong> - These workouts include cardio components to trigger endurance stimuli. Try to perform the whole workout without resting between exercises. Never compromise on form, even if you fight for a better time.</li>\n	<li><strong>HIIT runs</strong> - You want those six pack abs and want to look well trained and ripped. Your solution is HIIT runs. You will find them in your workout plan to increase your overall endurance and boost your metabolism. Don’t skip them if you are hunting your six pack abs.</li>\n	<li><strong>Skill raids </strong>– Skill raids are extra workout sessions which address essential muscles to get your raid done and get you closer to the skills you want to learn first. Skill raids are special and demanding workouts that can only be accessed by having the coach.</li>\n</ol>\n<strong>Progression Formula Feedback</strong>\n\n<u>Workout days</u>\n\nQuality over quantity is our simple rule for setting your workout days. Start with low numbers in the beginning, we recommend a minimum of two up to three workout days for the first couple weeks. As you progress you can intensify your experience, however don’t be overambitious but patient.\n\n<u>Limitations</u>\n\nLet the coach know when you have teared muscles or other severe limitations. We will give your affected muscles a break and challenge you in other ways. Please always look out for your health and safety and listen to the signals your body sends you. Bring the patience to work through progressions consistently and don’t move up the ladder to fast. Be aware that setting limitations significantly harms your weekly Ykings experience as you will not be able to have the full variety to progress at used speed.\n\n<u>Intensity</u>\n\nYour intensity depends on your feedback at the end of the week. The first weeks will be tough and we recommend doing less intense workout weeks with a max of three workouts per week in the beginning. Let your body adjust in a healthy way to the pace and workload of Ykings workouts.\n\n<u>Lean, athletic, strong</u>\n\nYkings workouts have three different focus tracks. Each of them includes another level of workout composition to challenge you according to your goals.\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Lean:</strong> In accordance to build strength this track focuses on strength endurance and we recommend starting it if you are a beginner and if you intend to get in shape first.</li>\n	<li><strong>Athletic:</strong> This focus track focuses on explosive strength and power. If you are an advanced athlete and just want to push for the next level, this track is for you.</li>\n	<li><strong>Strong: </strong>Strong focuses on absolute strength and provides the perfect layout to raid your skill successfully.</li>\n</ul>\nMix and vary each focus track in your workout plan to set different training stimuli. Try it out and find the track that suits you most.','Coach Philosophy','','publish','closed','closed','','coach-philosophy','','','2016-04-06 12:54:44','2016-04-06 12:54:44','',0,'http://ykings.com/?page_id=1194',0,'page','',0),(1199,1,'2016-04-15 05:38:18','2016-04-15 05:38:18','After reading this article you will know\n<ul>\n	<li>what makes the pullup an essential exercise</li>\n	<li>why you should aim for perfect form and technique</li>\n	<li>which variations and progressions will help your development</li>\n</ul>\nOne of the most popular exercises in bodyweight training is the pullup. It is a popular exercise and appears in all kind of workout plans. You will come across pullups in various sports whether it is calisthenics, CrossFit, bodybuilding or power lifting, it is an essential move. Although the pullup is a wanted exercise of many it’s difference is embedded in its form and its variations. A pullup performed in fitness studios and one performed in streetworkout varies significantly, but we will cover proper form in this article.\n\nAt Ykings and in calisthenics the pullup is a basic and essential exercise that qualifies you to learn more advanced movements as well. The effectiveness, its simplicity and applicability inside a home and health clubs but also outside with any object in calisthenics parks is one reason to master this exercise right in the beginning.\n\nAnother reason to learn the pullup is its effectiveness and the muscle groups it targets. You hardly can deny the usefulness of a pullup and its variations if you target a strong back, biceps, latissimus, neck and underarm. If done with perfect form you whole body will be engaged and target also other muscles like your core. Furthermore, it is the perfect counter exercise to push-ups and enables you for many static holds such as the human flag, front and back lever.\n\nQuality form is an absolute must not only for getting respected but also to work muscle memory correctly. Strict and pure pullups like those of calisthenics and gymnastics require a clean range of motion. Bad form can actually have a negative effect on your progress. Work with a spotter early on and perfect the movement.\n\nWhat is a clean pullup?\n\nFirst of all, there are many variations of the pullup and each of them triggers different muscles, however the original clean form of a pullup is what you should start aiming for in the beginning. This means you need to clean it up. Good form is mandatory to get the best out of you and the exercise. A strict and clean pullup is a pullup with an overhand grip on a horizontal bar. Your starting position is the deadhang with extended arms and a retracted shoulder (bringing shoulder blades together). Start pulling up and bring your chin above bar level without using any dynamic movement like swinging your legs. For one rep go slowly back in a deadhang position. One thing to look out for in the beginning is definitely locking out your arms in the deadhang. Even though you just stay there briefly this is of main importance as others would cheat by only going half way and not having the full effect of the pullup movement.\n\nCheck off the following list to perform the pullup correctly.\n<ul>\n	<li>Overhand grip at shoulder width</li>\n	<li>Engaged lower back and core</li>\n	<li>Shoulders back and chest forward</li>\n	<li>Legs straight or bend, but not crossed</li>\n	<li>Controlled movement, no swinging</li>\n	<li>Head over the bar</li>\n	<li>Deadhang (fully locked out arms)</li>\n</ul>\nIn the beginning you most certainly will not have the strength or the patience to perform the pullup in a perfect form. The solution is to progress and evolve to it over time. Aim for clean repetitions and be patient. There is enough to work on early on. With the right progressions and some dedication, you will get there soon.\n\nVariations are not only good to trigger different muscles or fight general boredom with the exercise but also to progress to tougher progressions and other elite movements.\n\nA popular variation of the pullup is the chinup. The main difference here is the grip position and muscle focus. The chinup requires an underhand grip and will also engage your biceps muscle, making them slightly easier in the beginning than the pullup. You can modify and be creative with the pullup and the chinup once you mastered one clean rep. Place your hands either wide and narrow and also play around with over and underhand grips.\n\nGetting started should not be the problem as the earlier progressions suit everyone with any fitness level. Furthermore, you have options to work on your plyometric and explosive power or on your total strength. We will cover all progressions and other exercises in a separate article soon. Take the time and think about where you want to go and which personal needs you want to address.\n\n<strong><em>Using the Ykings smartphone app will not only gradually develop you to master all different progressions, it will also focus on your individual goal of training. The options to go for are:</em></strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong><em>Lean – focus on strength development and muscle endurance</em></strong></li>\n	<li><strong><em>Athletic – focus on explosive strength</em></strong></li>\n	<li><strong><em>Strong – focus on maximum strength</em></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<strong><em>Finally, it is essential that you work on your form, gain strength over time and evolve to new movements gradually. Increase your body awareness and flexibility along the way with fully personalized workout plans fitting your needs. Join the community – #WeGrowTogether #StriveForProgress</em></strong>','Everything you need to know about a proper pullup','','publish','open','open','','everything-you-need-to-know-about-a-proper-pullup','','','2016-04-15 05:38:18','2016-04-15 05:38:18','',0,'http://ykings.com/?p=1199',0,'post','',0),(1200,1,'2016-04-15 05:34:08','2016-04-15 05:34:08','','File Apr 15, 12 31 13 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','file-apr-15-12-31-13-pm','','','2016-04-15 05:34:08','2016-04-15 05:34:08','',1199,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/File-Apr-15-12-31-13-PM.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1261,1,'2016-05-13 11:40:43','2016-05-13 11:40:43','','001','','inherit','open','closed','','001-3','','','2016-05-13 11:40:43','2016-05-13 11:40:43','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/001.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1262,1,'2016-05-27 09:38:12','2016-05-27 09:38:12','','Pages','','publish','closed','closed','','pages','','','2016-05-27 09:38:12','2016-05-27 09:38:12','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/index.php/2016/05/27/pages/',9,'nav_menu_item','',0),(1263,1,'2016-05-27 09:38:12','2016-05-27 09:38:12','','Shortcodes','','publish','closed','closed','','shortcodes','','','2016-05-27 09:38:12','2016-05-27 09:38:12','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/index.php/2016/05/27/sho