"http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FullSizeRender.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1122\"><img class=\" wp-image-1122\" src=\"http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FullSizeRender-624x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Power Competition @barwarz Berlin +24kg pullups\" width=\"483\" height=\"793\" /></a> Power Competition @barwarz Berlin +24kg pullups[/caption]\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n\r\nSpending quality time with my crew (barliner_workout), my motivation comes from working out in the park clearing my mind with a few sets after a stressful day. Sometimes it\'s hard to get your ass up, but just remember how awesome it feels when you finish up your final reps and be done with your workout. Even more motivation kicks in when you mastered the next step or nailed a new skill the first time. When it comes to training attituded, consistency and persistance is the name of the game.\r\n\r\nSometimes it\'s also the mirror that motivates me. Looking at yourself and realising that you are in full control of how you want to look like is a great feeling. So if you need some motivation and can\'t find it, I am here to share some with you!\r\n\r\nP.S. We will not skip leg day, but we can cry together afterwards.\r\n\r\nFind me in the app under micha_bln_\r\n\r\n</div>','micha_bln_: It\'s all about reps and sets','','publish','closed','closed','','portfolio-1','','','2016-06-10 10:49:49','2016-06-10 10:49:49','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=post-portfolio&#038;p=1355',0,'post-portfolio','',0),(1357,1,'2016-06-01 12:52:17','2016-06-01 12:52:17','[vc_row paddingtop=\"0\" paddingbottom=\"0\" css=\".vc_custom_1464775260573{padding-right: 0px !important;padding-left: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column][promoboxnew][promoboxnew_item title=\"FITNESS CLASSES\" background=\"909\" link=\"#\"]SIGNUP TODAY\r\n\r\nFIRST CLASS GYM[/promoboxnew_item][promoboxnew_item title=\"BOXING CLUB\" backgr