adually for bigger tasks. In PBT you will be guided with gradual steps to master difficult movements and skills. In essence an elite skill is divided into sub-exercises called progressions. Mastering progressions and ultimately your wanted skill over time is what progressive bodyweight training is all about.','What is progressive bodyweight training?','','publish','open','closed','','what-is-progressive-bodyweight-training','','','2016-06-07 11:51:16','2016-06-07 11:51:16','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1448',0,'ufaq','',0),(1449,1,'2016-06-07 11:54:26','2016-06-07 11:54:26','The beauty of bodyweight training is that it almost needs no equipment. All you need to start is a pullup bar and at best a set of sturdy parallettes or gymnastic rings. With the smartphone app you will have your workout plan with you anywhere you go. Train alone at home or together with others in one of the many workout parks around you. The required equipment is specified for each workout. All needed equipment can also be substituted by the things you have at home. Finally we recommend using resistance bands to help you with certain progressions and skills as well as with mobility exercises.','What kind of equipment is required?','','publish','open','closed','','what-kind-of-equipment-is-required','','','2016-09-05 07:54:14','2016-09-05 07:54:14','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1449',0,'ufaq','',0),(1450,1,'2016-06-07 11:55:59','2016-06-07 11:55:59','Although Ykings PBT looks somewhat intimidating, it is actually made for all fitness levels. If you’re healthy enough to exercise, you can start Ykings PBT. The adaptive nature and the flexibility of the workout concept with its progressions gives athletes of any fitness and skill level a way to start and excel in the future.','Am I too old? Too fat? Too inexperienced?','','publish','open','closed','','am-i-too-old-too-fat-too-inexperienced','','','2016-09-05 07:50:52','2016-09-05 07:50:52','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1450',0,'ufaq','',0),(1451,1,'2016-06-07 11:57:15','2016-06-07 11:57:15','We have developed Ykings Pro for those of you, who seek an adaptive workout concept or want to pursue skills while getting strong and fit. YkingsPro includes the following points:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Access to all workouts, skills, progressions and HIIT runs</li>\r\n 	<li>Weekly workout plans which dynamically adapt to your feedback (availability, workout intensity, skill- and fitness level)</li>\r\n 	<li>Full fletched workout days with warmups, fundamentals (pre-workout), strength &amp;HIIT-strength workouts and stretching routines</li>\r\n 	<li>Special designed skill raids – pick your wanted skill and encounter professional skill trainings to push your progress</li>\r\n 	<li>Progression formula - master elite skills (muscleup, front lever, human flag and more) with essential step by step progressions integrated in your workouts</li>\r\n 	<li>Guidance - all progressions and exercises include video tutorials and pro tips</li>\r\n 	<li>Freestyle function – track your own workout sessions and log them in your profile</li>\r\n 	<li>Ykings Community – receive tips and tricks from other athletes, friends and featured athletes &amp; find athletes and trainings spots close to you</li>\r\n</ul>','What is the benefit of YkingsPro (Coach)?','','publish','open','closed','','what-is-the-benefit-of-ykings-pro-coach','','','2016-09-05 07:45:25','2016-09-05 07:45:25','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1451',0,'ufaq','',0),(1452,1,'2016-06-07 11:58:34','2016-06-07 11:58:34','Sure. Ykings is a workout concept that can be easily combined with other training programs and sports. Ykings PBT will provide you with physical strength, more flexibility and resistance that will benefit your performance in other sports and training programs. Just make sure you don’t over train and take the appropriate rest days.','Can I combine Ykings PBT with other training programs and sports?','','publish','open','closed','','can-i-combine-ykings-with-other-training-programs-and-sports','','','2016-09-05 07:43:56','2016-09-05 07:43:56','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1452',0,'ufaq','',0),(1453,1,'2016-06-07 11:59:55','2016-06-07 11:59:55','Yes, although Ykings PBT is highly adaptive to your workout needs and is influenced by the goals you pursue, you will build <strong>strong lean muscle</strong>. Ykings PBT is not about extensive muscle mass like you might expect from bodybuilding. Our main focus is to build insane strength to perform elite bodyweight skills.','Will I build muscle with Ykings PBT?','','publish','open','closed','','will-i-build-muscle-with-ykings','','','2016-09-05 07:41:48','2016-09-05 07:41:48','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1453',0,'ufaq','',0),(1454,1,'2016-06-07 12:02:17','2016-06-07 12:02:17','Focus tracks are a first parameter for setting up the perfect workout plan for you. Follow a specific track to build different kinds of strength, get in shape, progress with new challenges and directly influence your workout week.\r\n\r\n<strong>LEAN:</strong> In accordance to build strength this track focuses on strength endurance and we recommend starting with the lean track, if you are a beginner and if you intend or have to get in shape first.\r\n\r\n<strong>ATHLETIC:</strong> The athletic track focuses on speed strength and power. If you are an advanced athlete and just want to push for the next level, this track is for you.\r\n\r\n<strong>STRONG: </strong>Strong focuses on absolute strength and provides the perfect layout to raid your skill successfully.','Which is the right focus tracks for me?','','publish','open','closed','','what-are-the-focus-tracks-for','','','2016-09-06 09:21:30','2016-09-06 09:21:30','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1454',0,'ufaq','',0),(1455,1,'2016-06-07 12:05:30','2016-06-07 12:05:30','<span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\',\'sans-serif\';\">As soon as you can perform the current progression as outlined in the workouts and videos, you can activate the next progression and start working on it. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\',\'sans-serif\';\">In general, the leaner and smaller you are the faster you will progress through calisthenics skills. In average a person advances every 4-6 weeks, assuming consistent and diligent work each week. After all just be very comfortable with the current progression and you will be more than ready to move on.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\',\'sans-serif\';\">Always remember to go back to an earlier progression to relief and finish up the set in case you are not able to finish the set with your newly activated progression.</span>','When to move on to the next progression?','','publish','open','closed','','when-do-i-move-to-the-next-progression','','','2016-09-05 07:18:44','2016-09-05 07:18:44','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1455',0,'ufaq','',0),(1456,1,'2016-06-07 12:07:58','2016-06-07 12:07:58','Fundamentals are considered to be a pre-workout, extended warmup and mobillity work. Fundamentals help you to additionally condition and strengthen specific parts of your body and get adjusted to the workouts ahead. There are special fundamentals that focus on mobility, flexibility and very specific basic skill work. Work your way through the regimen each day to hone your skills, perfect each movement and be properly warmed up.','What is the purpose of “Fundamentals” in a workout day?','','publish','open','closed','','what-is-the-purpose-of-fundamentals-in-a-workout-day','','','2016-09-05 07:17:24','2016-09-05 07:17:24','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1456',0,'ufaq','',0),(1457,1,'2016-06-07 12:12:54','2016-06-07 12:12:54','Activating a raid for a specific skill will set a priority on that bodyweight skill in the upcoming workout week. You will receive special designed skill trainings for the activated raid. Skill trainings are very demanding and will test your willingness to learn the skill. You can activate a raid for an elite skill in your personal “Skills”-section in the upper right corner.','What is the “Raid” function and how to activate it?','','publish','open','closed','','what-is-the-raid-function-and-how-to-activate-it','','','2016-09-05 07:15:56','2016-09-05 07:15:56','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1457',0,'ufaq','',0),(1458,1,'2016-06-07 12:13:55','2016-06-07 12:13:55','This is a very individual question and depends on your strength, endurance and level of fitness. In average the workouts take around 35 minutes, considering a solid warmup and stretching routine the time needed can vary.','How long in average will the workouts take?','','publish','open','closed','','how-long-in-average-will-the-workouts-take','','','2016-09-05 07:11:52','2016-09-05 07:11:52','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1458',0,'ufaq','',0),(1459,1,'2016-06-07 12:15:02','2016-06-07 12:15:02','You can\'t and you shouldn\'t. You will progress fastest and healthiest if you follow the workout days as laid out. In this way we can ensure the most efficient development and avoid overtraining of specific areas in your body. Please take your regeneration phases seriously.','Can you switch the order of workout days in the workout plan?','','publish','open','closed','','can-you-switch-the-order-of-workout-days-in-the-workout-plan','','','2016-09-05 07:10:47','2016-09-05 07:10:47','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1459',0,'ufaq','',0),(1460,1,'2016-06-07 12:17:53','2016-06-07 12:17:53','<span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\',\'sans-serif\';\">Newly activated progressions should be attacked with care. Don’t sacrifice form to do the last repetition. Always watch the video tutorial and check out our blog and knowledge base for additional information. Substitute with your already mastered progressions to finish up the set in case you cannot with the new activated progression.</span>','How do I handle new activated progressions in my training?','','publish','open','closed','','how-do-i-handle-new-activated-progressions-in-my-training','','','2016-09-05 07:09:43','2016-09-05 07:09:43','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1460',0,'ufaq','',0),(1461,1,'2016-06-07 12:19:57','2016-06-07 12:19:57','Please follow the rule of thumb of taking a rest day in between workout days. For beginners and even advanced athletes we recommend not going beyond 3-4 workout days per week. Progressive bodyweight training is very demanding especially if you are in the midst of mastering a skill. Please read also the Q&amp;A on overtraining, take sufficient rest days and listen to your body at all times.','Can I do this every day?','','publish','open','closed','','can-i-do-this-every-day','','','2016-09-05 07:08:11','2016-09-05 07:08:11','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1461',0,'ufaq','',0),(1462,1,'2016-06-07 12:22:33','2016-06-07 12:22:33','It really depends where you are starting and where you are going. When you start to exercise and getting comfortable with the workouts, you should recognize first changes within the first 3-4 weeks. Assuming your diet is in check as well, you will progress even faster if you are in great shape. Reaching your ultimate fitness is not goal but a given at Ykings. Results and goals are achieved fastest by those athletes who exercise consistently and don’t get injured while doing it. Take your workout days and regeneration phase serious and see for yourself.','How soon will I see results?','','publish','open','closed','','how-soon-will-i-see-results','','','2016-09-05 07:07:15','2016-09-05 07:07:15','',0,'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1462',0,'ufaq','',0),(1463,1,'2016-06-07 17:44:20','2016-06-07 17:44:20','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Ykings GmbH</strong>\nSchöllerstr.13\n72160 Horb am Neckar\nGermany\ninfo(a)ykings.co