inherit','closed','closed','','640-revision-v1','','','2016-06-10 13:56:10','2016-06-10 13:56:10','',640,'http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/06/10/640-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1606,1,'2016-06-10 14:04:40','2016-06-10 14:04:40','After reading this article you will know\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>why rings are a mandatory tool to implement</li>\r\n	<li>the non-training benefits of rings</li>\r\n	<li>how to get started with rings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nGymnastics rings are showing up in more gyms than ever before. Functional training is becoming very popular and you can observe the shift most probably in your current gym. The good thing, you can also easily setup rings at home yourself and there are a lot of reasons to do it. Many people mistakenly believe these wooden implements are only useful for athletes who use them in competition, like gymnasts or CrossFit athletes. However in reality, anyone can use the rings and benefit from them tremendously, because they help simultaneously build strength, stability, and coordination like no other apparatus. What you may not know about rings, though, is how effectively they build more than just upper body strength, muscular size and definition. Exercises are more valuable on rings than on pull up bars. Why? Compare a muscle up on a pullup bar and a muscle up on rings. Rings cover most of the exercises that you can do with a pullup bar, but it gives you also <strong><u>additional challenges</u></strong> in balancing and control. Overall that <strong><u>benefits your body awareness and control</u></strong>. So if you have room for a little investment or just thinking about getting a pullup bar, keep your eyes and mind also open for gymnastics rings.\r\n\r\nProfessional gymnasts show the whole spectrum of movements that can be performed with rings. They also show how much <strong><u>strength and concentration</u></strong> rings require to master. One of the great advantages of rings is that they <strong><u>require little space</u></strong> and are highly portable. Just compare packing either rings or a pullup bar in your luggage. We’ll bet you, you will choose the rings. Furthermore rings can <strong><u>be mounted quite flexibly</u></strong> and <strong><u>adjusted in height as easily as in width</u></strong>. This enables you to <strong><u>cover the most prestigious bodyweight exercises</u></strong> with one single apparatus anywhere you go.\r\n\r\nIf you are already a working out in the field of calisthenics you most probably have come across rings. For all those considering putting rings into their workout regimen, keep in mind that as with your progress with elite skills and moves, rings will require your patience and dedication. Accept rings as a challenge and push through. To get started to getting accustomed with rings start slowly transferring your usual routine to rings. Another way to acclimate with this new training style is by following this <strong><u>simple routine</u></strong>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"File-Feb-28-11-39-13-AM-e1456655976415.jpeg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1077\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1077\" src=\"File-Feb-28-11-39-13-AM-e1456655976415.jpeg\" alt=\"File Feb 01, 1 35 20 PM\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Top position holds – 3 rounds of 5-10 seconds\r\n</strong>Don’t forget to pack your shoulder when at the rings. Quality form at the rings is mandatory, so please take also a look at our “<a href=\"http://ykings.com/?p=1058\">what it actually means to pack your shoulders</a>” article for more information.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Ring Dips – 3 rounds of 3-5 reps</strong>\r\nFocus on good movement and explore the variety of muscles you can train by just positioning your upper body differently.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Australian Pullups – 3 rounds of 3-5 reps\r\n</strong>Australian Pullups are your go to move for effectively building the strength for pullups and chin-ups.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease warmup with a shoulder or joint dynamic stretching routine to prevent you from injury. Master your body control on rings first and after you feel a bit more comfortable using the rings, incorporate rings exercises into your regular training as you see a fit.\r\n\r\nHow have you used rings in your past? Ever considered to incorporate them in your workouts? What are your experiences while using rings? Has it changed your physique? Please leave a comment and join the discussion with us.\r\n\r\nPS: In one of our next articles, we will cover what you can learn from your failures and how it can benefit your life overall.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Ykings is a full body training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves. All exercises we provide are bodyweight exercises only and most of them can be done either with bars or rings. We are only days away before our Smartphone App will hit the stores. To be notified firsthand, subscribe to our mailing list. Get also informed about new articles like this to benefit your workouts. Learn, evolve, master.</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>#WeGrowTogether #StriveForProgress</em></strong>','Why you should implement rings in your workout routine','','inherit','closed','closed','','1068-revision-v1','','','2016-06-10 14:04:40','2016-06-10 14:04:40','',1068,'http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/06/10/1068-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1607,1,'2016-06-10 14:07:03','2016-06-10 14:07:03','After reading this article you will know\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>why rings are a mandatory tool to implement</li>\r\n	<li>the non-training benefits of rings</li>\r\n	<li>how to get started with rings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nGymnastics rings are showing up in more gyms than ever before. Functional training is becoming very popular and you can observe the shift most probably in your current gym. The good thing, you can also easily setup rings at home yourself and there are a lot of reasons to do it. Many people mistakenly believe these wooden implements are only useful for athletes who use them in competiti