e way of training. Luckily progressive bodyweight training is motivation in itself because you learn something new each session. The learning factor is also the number one reason you should consider training with others. A workout buddy can help you spot flaws in your form and technique, a trainer can give you tips to reach the next level and a workout group can give you a new challenge from time to time and be a lot of fun. Let them help you to achieve your fitness goals and enjoy the sessions. Go with a group of dedicated buddies if you want to be constantly motivated and supported. If you are more up for a competition and strive more under those circumstances, consider working out with others.\r\n\r\nJust think about what type of person you are and use each option smartly. Understand alone workouts and with others as a tactical tool to reach your goals faster. Enjoy!\r\n\r\nWe are sure we missed a couple of good other reasons. Leave us a comment and let’s talk about this. Which type of training person are you?\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Ykings is progressive bodyweight training. Learn elite skills like muscleups, handstand pushups or the human flag among other epic moves step by step. Subscribe to the coach for personalized workout weeks and raid the skills you want to learn with specific skill training. Exercise alone in the shadows, reach out to the community in the app, ask a featured athlete and join us via <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/official.ykings/\">Facebook</a> in one of our many public workout sessions.</em></strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Working out alone versus working out with others','','inherit','closed','closed','','1666-revision-v1','','','2016-06-30 14:53:41','2016-06-30 14:53:41','',1666,'http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/06/30/1666-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1676,1,'2016-07-04 09:34:15','2016-07-04 09:34:15','Ykings is mainly based on the disciplines <a href=\"http://ykings.com/index.php/what-is-calisthenics/\">calisthenics</a> and gymnastics. Both sports are reknown for the most demanding and challenging skills and moves in bodyweight training.<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nMastering a skill requires to go at it step by step. The adaptive nature of the sport and your progress towards a skill is embedded in essential exercises called progressions. This is why at Ykings we talk about progressive bodyweight training.\r\n\r\nProgressive bodyweight training (PBT) secures gradual development towards advanced bodyweight exercises and elite skills such as the muscleup, human flag, front lever and many more.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of the Ykings workout concept is to guide you efficiently and healthy towards mastering your most desirable bodyweight skills. Consider to workout not only for your fitness, but strength, body control and skills at the same time.\r\n\r\n<em>#StriveForProgress</em>','The sport behind Ykings','','inherit','closed','closed','','616-revision-v1','','','2016-07-04 09:34:15','2016-07-04 09:34:15','',616,'http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/07/04/616-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1677,1,'2016-07-04 09:38:06','2016-07-04 09:38:06','','007','','inherit','open','closed','','007-2','','','2016-07-04 09:38:06','2016-07-04 09:38:06','',1415,'http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/007.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1678,1,'2016-07-04 09:38:33','2016-07-04 09:38:33','','Jogging in couple','Young couple running in park.','inherit','open','closed','','jogging-in-couple','','','2016-07-04 09:38:33','2016-07-04 09:38:33','',1415,'http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/iStock_000072914711_Large.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1679,1,'2016-07-04 10:09:41','2016-07-04 10:09:41','<span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Gymnastics</strong></span> as an Olympic event have been so far the most well-developed form of bodyweight skills. This wide recognition and popularity makes Gymnastics the most influential form of bodyweight training.\r\n\r\nAlthough gymnastics is by itself a broad term and contains a variety of different disciplines… the main goal is to develop a large variety of athletic qualities, such us strength, agility, coordination, flexibility, self-control, kinesthetic awareness, etc. For this reason Gymnastics builds the core of <strong><a href=\"http://ykings.com/smartphone-application/\">Ykings PBT</a></strong> and is probably the mother of <strong><a href=\"http://ykings.com/what-is-calisthenics/\">bodyweight training</a></strong>.\r\n\r\nMost gymnasts and bodyweight athletes are in an amazing physical shape. Our athletes are among the strongest and most flexible on a pound for pound comparsion. This is the main reason why the sport is attractive for everybody out there who ultimately does not want to look like a bodybuilder. Build natural lean muscles while you work on other athletic qualities.\r\n\r\nGymnastics includes a wide variety of exercises and insane skills. At Ykings we combined both worlds and embedded the versatility of Gymnastics in a progressive bodyweight training platform.','Gymnastics','','publish','closed','closed','','competitive-gymnastics','','','2016-08-30 12:08:41','2016-08-30 12:08:41','',0,'http://ykings.com/?page_id=1679',0,'page','',0),(1680,1,'2016-07-04 10:09:41','2016-07-04 10:09:41','Gymnastics as an Olympic event have been so far the most well-developed form of calisthenics training. This wide recognition and popularity makes gymnastics the most influential form of bodyweight training.\r\n\r\nAlthough gymnastics is by itself a broad term and contains a variety of different disciplines… the main goal is to develop a large variety of athletic qualities, such us strength, agility, coordination, flexibility, self-control, kinesthetic awareness, etc. For this reason Gymnastics builds the core of Ykings and is probably the mother of <a href=\"http://ykings.com/index.php/what-is-calisthenics/\"><b>calisthenics.</b></a>\r\n\r\nMost gymnasts and calisthenics athletes are in an amazing physical shape. Our athletes are among the strongest and most flexible on a pound for pound comparsion. This is the main reason why the sport is attractive for everybody out there who ultimately does not want to look like a bodybuilder. Build natural lean muscles while you work on other athletic qualities.\r\n\r\nGymnastics includes a wide variety of exercises and insane skills. At Ykings we combined both worlds and embedded the versatility of gymnastics in a progressive bodyweight training platform.','Competitive Gymnastics','','inherit','closed','closed','','1679-revision-v1','','','2016-07-04 10:09:41','2016-07-04 10:09:41','',1679,'http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/07/04/1679-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1681,1,'2016-08-29 17:01:53','2016-08-29 17:01:53','<div id=\"cc-m-8363560395\" class=\"j-module n j-text \">\n\nBodyweight training refers to exercises that are done in a rhythmic, systematic way using your body weight for resistance. An advanced form of <strong>bodyweight training </strong>is calisthenics, which is also known as street workout.\n\n<em>The word calisthenics comes from the ancient Greek words kálos (κάλλος), which means \"beauty\", and sthénos (σθένος), meaning \"strength\". Calisthenics is raw and pure bodyweight training and also known as Street Workout.</em>\n\nThe benefits of bodyweight training are translated into Ykings PBT\n<ol>\n 	<li>One of the greatest advantages of bodyweight training is that you can do it anywhere, anytime.</li>\n 	<li>There are easier and more advanced exercises to start or evolve with that makes the sport suitable for athletes of all skill and fitness levels.</li>\n 	<li>Beginners as well as advanced athletes will find a goal to pursue with the sport. Besides the standard claims of many sports and fitness programms, bodyweight training does not only increase your general fitness and get you in great shape, but provides multiple benefits in addition for you.</li>\n 	<li>Proper bodyweight training will promote the growth of lean muscle mass, and increase your strength, mobility, flexibility, agility, and endurance.</li>\n</ol>\nAs you see from the list of benefits of the sport, there is a fine line to <strong><a href=\"http://ykings.com/index.php/competitive-gymnastics/\">competitive gymnastics</a></strong>. In the Ykings workout concept we embedded the adaptive nature of the sport in a comprehensive progressive bodyweight training concept. If you want to be more than just fit, let us hunt down skills and evolve you to a bodyweight master. Welcome to our world.\n\n</div>','Bodyweight Training & Calisthenics','','inherit','closed','closed','','1415-autosave-v1','','','2016-08-29 17:01:53','2016-08-29 17:01:53','',1415,'http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/07/04/1415-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1682,1,'2016-07-04 10:15:27','2016-07-04 10:15:27','<div id=\"cc-m-8363560395\" class=\"j-module n j-text \">\r\n\r\nCalisthenics is disguised in other sports, particularly gymnastics. It refers to exercises that are done in a rhythmic, systematic way using the body weight for resistance. So calisthenics is just another name for bodyweight training.\r\n\r\nThe word <strong><i>calisthenics</i></strong> comes from the ancient Greek words <i>kálos</i> (κάλλος), which means \"beauty\", and <i>sthénos</i> (σθένος), meaning \"strength\". Calisthenics is raw and pure bodyweight training and also known as Street Workout.\r\n\r\nOne of the greatest advantages of bodyweight training is that you can do it anywhere, anytime, and there are easier and more advanced exercises to start or evolve with.\r\n\r\nBeginners as well as advanced athletes will find a goal to pursue with the sport. Besides the standard claims of many sports and fitness programms, calisthenics does not only increase your general fitness and get you in great shape, but provides multiple benefits in addition for you.\r\n\r\nProper calisthenics training will promote the growth of lean muscle mass, and increase your strength, mobility, flexibility, agility, and endurance.\r\n\r\nAs you see from the list of benefits of the sport, there is a fine line to <a href=\"http://ykings.com/index.php/competitive-gymnastics/\">competitive gymnastics</a>. In the Ykings workout concept we embedded the adaptive nature of the sport in a comprehensive progressive bodyweight training concept. If you want to be more than just fit, let us hunt down skills and evolve you to a bodyweight master. Welcome to our world.\r\n\r\n</div>','Calisthenics','','inherit','closed','closed','','1415-revision-v1','','','2016-07-04 10:15:27','2016-07-04 10:15:27','',1415,'http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/07/04/1415-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1683,1,'2016-07-04 10:17:57','2016-07-04 10:17:57',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','1683','','','2016-07-04 10:18:56','2016-07-04 10:18:56','',0,'http://ykings.com/?p=1683',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(1684,1,'2016-07-04 10:30:53','2016-07-04 10:30:53','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Learn calisthenics with Ykings</strong></p>\r\nYKMS stands for Ykings Mannfall Sessions. YKMS are free public workout sessions which are offered to create interest of the gereal public in the sport. We are supporting local groups to offer YKMS as a introduction to the sport with a set standard.\r\n\r\nThe mission is to help all athletes of different fitness and skill levels to progress to the next level or simply get a feeling what the sport is all about.\r\n\r\nYKMS provides a unique and valuable social education and experience to the world of gymnastics and calisthenics. It provides an ideal opportunity to learn about teamwork; sportsmanship; fair play and dedication.\r\n\r\nThe time required to master the fundamental skills requires a great amount of patience, dedication, perseverance and planning. YKMS follow a simple schedule that is altered a bit by the local groups which looks like this.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>warmup</li>\r\n 	<li>mobility session</li>\r\n 	<li>skill training and progression class with pull/dip/core&amp;leg stations</li>\r\n 	<li>workout challenge</li>\r\n 	<li>cooldown &amp; stretching</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nEverybody is welcome, we always have a beginner class that gets an introduction to the sport, so feel free to join us. Check our <strong><a href=\"http://ykings.com/New/index.php/our-events/\">events webpage</a></strong> or sign in over facebook.\r\n\r\n[facebook id=\"facebook_53\" links=\"https://www.facebook.com/official.ykings/\" width=\"\" layout=\"standard\" colorscheme=\"light\" sendbutton=\"false\" showfaces=\"false\" ]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in getting YKMS to your city,<strong> <a href=\"http://ykings.com/New/index.php/contact/\">contact us</a></strong>. Become a partner and do your part to bring the sport forward.','YKMS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1424-revision-v1','','','2016-07-04 10:30:53','2016-07-04 10:30:53','',1424,'http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/07/04/1424-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1685,1,'2016-07-06 10:48:26','2016-07-06 10:48:26','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Get ready to be pushed\r\n</strong></p>\r\nYkings is divided in a basic free version and YkingsPro with a subscription based dynamic personal Coach.\r\n<div id=\"ufaq-body-3r7-1451-11\" class=\"ufaq-faq-body ufaq-body-1451\">\r\n<div id=\"ufaq-post-1451\" class=\"ewd-ufaq-post-margin ufaq-faq-post\">\r\n\r\nIn the free version of Ykings you can try multiple workouts, engage with the community and get a feeling what Ykings is all about.\r\n\r\nWe have developed YkingsPro for those of you, who seek an adaptive path to work on their body transformation, simply want to pursue skills while getting strong and fit. YkingsPro includes the following benefits compared to the free version:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>No limits</strong> - access all workouts, excercises, skills, progressions and HIIT runs</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Personalized workout plans</strong> - take advantage of weekly workout plans which are dynamically adapted to your feedback\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>availability</li>\r\n 	<li>workout intensity</li>\r\n 	<li>focus track</li>\r\n 	<li>raids</li>\r\n 	<li>skill- and fitness level</li>\r\n 	<li>goals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Full workout days</strong> - progress in a healthy way. Get various warmups, fundamentals (pre-workout, dynamic stretching and mobility), workouts (circuit-, sets &amp; reps training) and stretching routines</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Skill raids</strong> – pick your wanted skill and receive professional skill trainings to push your progress to the next level</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Progression formula</strong> – master elite skills (muscleup, front lever, human flag and more) with essential step by step progressions and ally exercises automatically integrated in your workouts</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Guidance</strong> – all progressions and exercises include video tutorials with pro tips and range of motion</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Freestyle</strong> – track your own workout sessions and log them in your profile</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Community</strong> – share &amp; receive tips and tricks from other athletes, friends and featured athletes &amp; find athletes and trainings spots around to you</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/app-banner.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1545\" src=\"http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/app-banner-1024x638.jpg\" alt=\"app-banner\" width=\"900\" height=\"561\" /></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','What to expect from the app?','','inherit','closed','closed','','620-revision-v1','','','2016-07-06 10:48:26','2016-07-06 10:48:26','',620,'http://ykings.com/index.php/2016/07/06/620-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1686,1,'2016-07-07 10:52:10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong>Form and technique - shoulders 1on1</strong>\r\n\r\nWhoever is starting out to hunt down advanced bodyweight skills will come across very important terminology that we also use in our video tutorials and blog posts. Following, we are covering the most important terms.\r\n\r\n<strong>Protraction and retraction</strong>\r\nProtraction and retraction (or abduction and adduction, respectively) are opposites. In protraction, the scapulae (aka shoulder blades) move forward and outwards from each other, while in retraction, the scapulae move backwards and towards each other.\r\n\r\nPlease see pictures below.\r\n\r\nPicture 1 Protraction              Picture 2 Retraction\r\n\r\nYou protract by pushing your shoulders forward, trying to touch them in front of your chest as you can see in a perfect pushup position.\r\n\r\nYou retract by squeezing the shoulderblades together as you can see here in a perfect deadhang on the bar.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Protraction is mainly important during planche work, while retracting is important in rows and other forms of horizontal pulling.</em></strong>\r\n\r\nTo isolate your joints and to be less injury prone there is two other shoulder positions for certain exercises you have to learn about.\r\n\r\n<strong>Depression and elevation</strong>\r\nDepressing the scapulae means you\'re moving them down towards your butt, like in a support hold. Elevation is the opposite, where the shoulder blades move up towards your head.\r\n\r\nPicture 1 Depression          Picture 2 Elevation\r\n\r\nYou depress by pushing your shoulders down, trying to get your arms as low as they can go like here in the L-Sit.\r\n\r\nYou elevate by pushing your shoulders up, as if you\'re trying to cover your ears as you can see here with a handstand.\r\n\r\n<strong>Depression is important during dipping, support holds, and L-sits. It\'s also important to do during horizontal pulling and pushing (to prevent shrugging up). Elevation is mainly important during handstand-related exercises.</strong>','Shoulder positioning demystified','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2016-07-07 10:52:10','2016-07-07 10:52:10','',0,'http://ykings.com/?page_id=1686',0,'page','',0),(1687,1,'2016-07-07 10:40:39','2