0,'http://ykings.com/640-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1750,1,'2016-08-30 10:43:26','2016-08-30 10:43:26','<span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Progressive Bodyweight Traininig</strong></span> is made of the disciplines <strong><a href=\"http://ykings.com/what-is-calisthenics/\">bodyweight training</a></strong> and <a href=\"http://ykings.com/index.php/competitive-gymnastics/\"><strong>gymnastics</strong></a>. Both sports are reknown for the most demanding body control and challenging bodyweight skills.<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nMastering a bodyweight skill requires a systematic step by step approach. The adaptive nature of the sport and the progress towards a skill is embedded in essential exercises called progressions. This is why our workout concept refers to progressive bodyweight training (PBT).\r\n\r\nProgressive bodyweight training (PBT) secures gradual development towards advanced bodyweight exercises and skills such as the muscleup, human flag, front lever to name a few.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of Ykings PBT is to guide you efficiently and healthy towards mastering your most desirable bodyweight skills. Consider to workout not only for your fitness, but strength, body control and skills and many more beneficial body characteristics at the same time.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><em>#StriveForProgress</em></span>','Progressive Bodyweight Training (PBT)','','inherit','closed','closed','','616-revision-v1','','','2016-08-30 10:43:26','2016-08-30 10:43:26','',616,'http://ykings.com/616-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1751,1,'2016-08-30 10:47:07','2016-08-30 10:47:07','<span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Gymnastics</strong></span> as an Olympic event have been so far the most well-developed form of bodyweight skills. This wide recognition and popularity makes Gymnastics the most influential form of bodyweight training.\r\n\r\nAlthough gymnastics is by itself a broad term and contains a variety of different disciplines… the main goal is to develop a large variety of athletic qualities, such us strength, agility, coordination, flexibility, self-control, kinesthetic awareness, etc. For this reason Gymnastics builds the core of <strong><a href=\"http://ykings.com/smartphone-application/\">Ykings PBT</a></strong> and is probably the mother of <strong><a href=\"http://ykings.com/what-is-calisthenics/\">bodyweight training</a></strong>.\r\n\r\nMost gymnasts and bodyweight athletes are in an amazing physical shape. Our athletes are among the strongest and most flexible on a pound for pound comparsion. This is the main reason why the sport is attractive for everybody out there who ultimately does not want to look like a bodybuilder. Build natural lean muscles while you work on other athletic qualities.\r\n\r\nGymnastics includes a wide variety of exercises and insane skills. At Ykings we combined both worlds and embedded the versatility of Gymnastics in a progressive bodyweight training platform.','Gymnastics','','inherit','closed','closed','','1679-revision-v1','','','2016-08-30 10:47:07','2016-08-30 10:47:07','',1679,'http://ykings.com/1679-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1752,1,'2016-08-31 13:27:22','2016-08-31 13:27:22','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Learn progressive bodyweight training with the community</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/1nPuqNWK8uU\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\">\r\n</iframe></p>\r\nYKMS stands for Ykings Mannfall Sessions. YKMS are free public workout sessions which are offered to create interest of the gereal public in the sport. We are supporting local groups to offer YKMS as a introduction to the sport with a set standard.\r\n\r\nThe mission is to help all athletes of different fitness and skill levels to progress to the next level or simply get a feeling of what the sport is all about.\r\n\r\nYKMS provides a unique and valuable social education and experience to the world of progressive bodyweight training. It provides an ideal opportunity to learn about teamwork, motivation, fun, sportsmanship and dedication.\r\n\r\nMastering bodyweight skills requires a great amount of patience, dedication, perseverance and planning. Prior to a YKMS, participants have the opportunity (via facebook) to vote for the bodyweight skills they want to learn.YKMS follow a simple schedule that is altered a bit by the local groups which looks like this.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Warmup</li>\r\n 	<li>Mobility ession</li>\r\n 	<li>Skill and progression training (according to community vote)</li>\r\n 	<li>HIIT &amp; full body workout</li>\r\n 	<li>Cooldown &amp; stretching</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nEverybody is welcome, we always have a beginner class that provides an introduction to the sport. Feel free to join us. Check our <strong><a href=\"http://ykings.com/New/index.php/our-events/\">events webpage</a></strong> or sign in over facebook.\r\n\r\n[facebook id=\"facebook_53\" links=\"https://www.facebook.com/official.ykings/\" width=\"\" layout=\"standard\" colorscheme=\"light\" sendbutton=\"false\" showfaces=\"false\" ]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in getting YKMS to your city,<strong> <a href=\"http://ykings.com/New/index.php/contact/\">contact us</a></strong>. Become a partner and do your part to bring the sport forward.','YKMS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1424-revision-v1','','','2016-08-31 13:27:22','2016-08-31 13:27:22','',1424,'http://ykings.com/1424-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1753,1,'2016-08-31 13:29:02','2016-08-31 13:29:02','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Get ready to be pushed\r\n</strong></p>\r\nYkings is divided in a free basic version and YkingsPro. YkingsPro includes a dynamic coach, who creates workout weeks and skill trainings on a subscription basis according to your prefernces.\r\n<div id=\"ufaq-body-3r7-1451-11\" class=\"ufaq-faq-body ufaq-body-1451\">\r\n<div id=\"ufaq-post-1451\" class=\"ewd-ufaq-post-margin ufaq-faq-post\">\r\n\r\nWe have developed YkingsPro for those of you, who seek an adaptive path to work on their body transformation and simply want to pursue skills while getting stronger and fitter. YkingsPro includes the following benefits compared to the free version:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>No limits</strong></span> - access all workouts, exercises, skills, progressions and HIIT runs</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Personalized workout plans</strong></span> - take advantage of weekly workout plans which are dynamically adapted to your feedback\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">availability</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">workout intensity</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">focus track</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">raids</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">skill- and fitness level</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">goals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Full workout days</strong></span> - progress in a healthy way. Get various warmups, fundamentals (pre-workout, dynamic stretching and mobility), workouts (circuit-, sets &amp; reps training) and stretching routines</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Skill raids</strong></span> – pick your wanted skill and receive professional skill trainings to push your progress to the next level</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Progression formula</strong></span> – master elite skills (muscleup, front lever, human flag and more) with essential step by step progressions and ally exercises automatically integrated in your workouts</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Guidance</strong></span> – all progressions and exercises include video tutorials with pro tips and range of motion</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Freestyle</strong></span> – track your own workout sessions and log them in your profile</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #f0b300;\"><strong>Community</strong></span> – share &amp; receive tips and tricks from other athletes, friends and featured athletes &amp; find athletes and trainings spots around to you</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/YKingsPro-vs-Free_EN_.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1746\" src=\"http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/YKingsPro-vs-Free_EN_-716x1024.png\" alt=\"YKingsPro vs Free_EN_\" width=\"716\" height=\"1024\" /></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','YkingsPro - This Is What You Can Expect','','inherit','closed','closed','','620-revision-v1','','','2016-08-31 13:29:02','2016-08-31 13:29:02','',620,'http://ykings.com/620-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1755,1,'2016-09-05 07:06:37','2016-09-05 07:06:37','It really depends where you are starting and where you are going. When you start to exercise and getting comfortable with the workouts, you should recognize first changes within the first 3-4 weeks. Assuming your diet is in check as well, you will only progress if you are in great shape. Reaching your ultimate fitness is not goal but a given at Ykings. Results and goals are achieved fastest by those athletes who exercise consistently and don’t get injured while doing it. Take your workout days and regeneration phase serious and see for yourself.','How soon will I see results?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1462-autosave-v1','','','2016-09-05 07:06:37','2016-09-05 07:06:37','',1462,'http://ykings.com/1462-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1756,1,'2016-09-05 07:09:41','2016-09-05 07:09:41','<span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\',\'sans-serif\';\">Newly activated progressions should be attacked with care. Don’t sacrifice form to do the last repetition. Always watch the video tutorial and check out our blog and knowledge base for additional information. Substitute with your already mastered progressions to finish up the set in case you cannot with the new activated progression.</span>','How do I handle new activated progressions in my training?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1460-autosave-v1','','','2016-09-05 07:09:41','2016-09-05 07:09:41','',1460,'http://ykings.com/1460-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1757,1,'2016-09-05 07:14:15','2016-09-05 07:14:15','Activating a raid for a specific skill will set a priority on that bodyweight skill in the upcoming workout week. You will receive special designed skill trainings for the activated raid. Skill trainings are very demanding and will test your willingness to learn the skill. You can activate a raid for an elite skill in your personal “Skills”-section. You will find it in the navigation bar in the apps.','What is the “Raid” function and how to activate it?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1457-autosave-v1','','','2016-09-05 07:14:15','2016-09-05 07:14:15','',1457,'http://ykings.com/1457-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1758,1,'2016-09-06 09:19:49','2016-09-06 09:19:49','Focus tracks are a first parameter for setting up the perfect workout plan for you. Follow a specific track to build different kinds of strength, get in shape, progress with new challenges and directly influence your workout week.\n\n<strong>LEAN:</strong> In accordance to build strength this track focuses on strength endurance and we recommend starting with the lean track, if you are a beginner and if you intend or have to get in shape first.\n\n<strong>ATHLETIC:</strong> The athletic track focuses on e strength and power. If you are an advanced athlete and just want to push for the next level, this track is for you..\n\nChoose <strong>STRONG</strong> if you are interested in max. strength, and focusing solely on skill training.','Which is the right focus tracks for me?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1454-autosave-v1','','','2016-09-06 09:19:49','2016-09-06 09:19:49','',1454,'http://ykings.com/1454-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1759,1,'2016-09-05 07:46:58','2016-09-05 07:46:58','Although looking If you’re healthy enough to exercise, you can start Ykings PBT. The adaptive nature and the flexibility of the workout concept with its progressions gives athletes of any fitness and skill level a way to start.','Am I too old? Too fat? Too inexperienced?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1450-autosave-v1','','','2016-09-05 07:46:58','2016-09-05 07:46:58','',1450,'http://ykings.com/1450-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1760,1,'2016-09-05 07:53:35','2016-09-05 07:53:35','The beauty of bodyweight training is that it almost needs no equipment. All you need to start is a pullup bar and at best a set of sturdy parallettes or gymnastic rings. With the smartphone app you will have your workout plan with you anywhere you go. Train alone at home or together with others in one of the many workout parks around you. The required equipment is specified for each workout. All needed equipment can also be substituted by the things you have at home. Finally we recommend using','What kind of equipment is required?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1449-autosave-v1','','','2016-09-05 07:53:35','2016-09-05 07:53:35','',1449,'http://ykings.com/1449-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1761,1,'2016-09-05 07:56:32','2016-09-05 07:56:32','Ykings PBT includes the most prominent bodyweight skills of gymnastics and advanced bodyweight training. Among others, you will have the opportunity to receive guided training towards bodyweight sills such as the human flag, front and back lever, L-Sit, handstand, One Arm Pushups and many more.','What skills & moves will I learn?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1447-autosave-v1','','','2016-09-05 07:56:32','2016-09-05 07:56:32','',1447,'http://ykings.com/1447-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1762,1,'2016-09-05 08:31:48','2016-09-05 08:31:48','Skill trainings have three different fitness, skill and capability levels that are labeled as “Hero”, “Barzerker” and “Legend”. Influence your skill training by activating new progressions in your skill sheet of the respective skill. We will always challenge you with newly activated progressions and skill trainings. Once you finish them within a workout week, the respective skill training will be available permanently in your skill training tab.','What are the intensitiy levels for skill training?','','publish','open','closed','','what-are-the-difficulties-and-intensities-for-skill-trainings','','','2016-09-06 09:15:15','2016-09-06 09:15:15','',0,'http://ykings.com/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1762',0,'ufaq','',0),(1763,1,'2016-09-05 09:02:07','2016-09-05 09:02:07','There are several parameters that influence your workout week.\r\n\r\n<strong>Focus track</strong>: The focus track determines the kind of training you will receive during your workout week. This can be adjusted weekly in the coach feedback.\r\n\r\n<strong>Activated progressions:</strong> Please be advised to have your skill sheet and the progressions you are capable of performing up to date at all times. Activate progressions by tapping on the progression sign, left to the exercise name.\r\n\r\n<strong>Raids:</strong> Select a raid to specify the focus of your skill training. Activate the raid button for a specific skill in the upper right corner of the wanted skill.\r\n\r\n<strong>Feedback:</strong> After finishing your workout week, you will have the chance to adjust intensities and the parameters above for your upcoming workout week.','How to setup my workout weeks? What to do with the skill sheet?','','publish','open','closed','','how-to-setup-my-workout-weeks-what-to-do-with-the-skill-sheet','','','2016-09-05 09:02:07','2016-09-05 09:02:07','',0,'http://ykings.com/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1763',0,'ufaq','',0),(1764,1,'2016-09-05 09:02:34','2016-09-05 09:02:34','With the MAX strength assessment we are checking whether you are capable of performing basic exercises or if we have to start on a beginner regimen with you. If you fail one of the exercises, the coach will put you in a specialized development program to be ready for skill trainings later on.','How does the MAX strength assessment influence my training?','','publish','open','closed','','how-does-the-max-strength-assessment-influence-my-training','','','2016-09-05 09:02:34','2016-09-05 09:02:34','',0,'http://ykings.com/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1764',0,'ufaq','',0),(1765,1,'2016-09-06 13:25:44','2016-09-06 13:25:44','<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>which traits of a resistance band are beneficial for you</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>how also advanced athletes can make use of resistance bands</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>where to utilize them in your skill training</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMany questions reached us regarding the use of resistance bands with Ykings PBT. In this blog post we will not only give you our take on resistance bands but also on how to make use of them in general.\r\n\r\nMost beginners find the static and dynamic skills (e.g. muscleups and front levers) challenging and intimidating. Never forget that you are looking at bodyweight masters who have trained very hard to perform and master those sills. You won’t perform the skill right away, but if you diligently work with Ykings PBT, we will get you there progressively. To structure our take on resistance bands, we will split the topic in a body strengthening &amp; supporting part and a mobility &amp; resistance part.\r\n\r\n<strong>Body strengthening &amp; supporting traits of a resistance band</strong>\r\n\r\nResistance bands can play a huge role in your development and strength building phase. Supporting aspects of resistance bands are to compensate the lack of joint stability and upper body strength in the beginning. Resistance bands are also very helpful with flexibility and mobility exercises that impact your personal warmups and pre-workouts.\r\n\r\nMoreover resistance bands will help you strengthening your body and building muscle memory. Later refers to mastering an exercise by practicing and stimulating your muscles over and over with the right range of motion locking in the correct form.\r\n\r\nRemoving “x” amount of pounds [or kg] from your own body weight, you can decrease but also increase resistance for many exercises.\r\n\r\nConsider the example of learning muscleups. To master muscleups, you must be able to perform pullups and straight bar dips. Learning a pullup is difficult and starts with a clear progression ladder as shown below. Every single time you personally struggle with an exercise in bodyweight training, you should consider using a band if possible. With the band you will gradually adjust to the strength needed and perform the exercise with improved form. Let’s have a look on how you could make use of a band learning muscleups.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Eccentric Pullups (can be done with a resistance band)</li>\r\n 	<li>Assisted Pullups (as shown in our video tutorials with a band)</li>\r\n 	<li>Pullups (Assisted Pullups are the little brother of pullups using a band)</li>\r\n 	<li>High Chest Pullups (can be done with a resistance band)</li>\r\n 	<li>Muscelups (can be done with a resistance band)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nFinally you can use resistance bands to add weight and increase resistance for certain exercises. If you are an advanced athlete, make use of your resistance bands whenever you practice different variations of push-ups, squats and dips.\r\n\r\n<strong>The most efficient tool for rapid progress in strength and making gradual improvements in technique for Ykings PBT is the resistance band. Other than that Ykings PBT is a progressive form of getting in tune with your body while you hunt down elite bodyweight skills. For each skill we have designed a clear progression ladder, so you will need to perform “A” before moving on to “B” and so on.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #f0b323;\"><strong>#StriveForProgress &amp; don’t forget #StrongIsTheNewSexy</strong></span>','Using resistance bands in bodyweight training','','publish','open','open','','using-resistance-bands-in-bodyweight-training','','','2016-09-06 13:25:44','2016-09-06 13:25:44','',0,'http://ykings.com/?p=1765',0,'post','',0),(1766,1,'2016-09-06 13:22:05','2016-09-06 13:22:05','<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>which traits of a resistance band are beneficial for you</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>how also advanced athletes can make use of resistance bands</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>where to utilize them in your skill training</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMany questions reached us regarding the use of resistance bands with Ykings PBT. In this blog post we will not only give you our take on resistance bands but also clarify how to make use of them.\r\n\r\nMost beginners find the static and dynamic skills (e.g. muscleups and front levers) challenging and intimidating. Never forget that you are looking at bodyweight masters who have trained very hard to perform and master those sills. You won’t perform the skill right away, but if you diligently work with Ykings PBT, we will get you there progressively. To structure our take on resistance bands, we will split the topic in a body strengthening &amp; supporting part and a mobility &amp; resistance part.\r\n\r\n<strong>Body strengthening &amp; supporting traits of a resistance band</strong>\r\n\r\nResistance bands can play a huge role in your development and strength building phase. Supporting aspects of resistance bands are to compensate the lack of joint stability and upper body strength in the beginning. Resistance bands are also very helpful with flexibility and mobility exercises that impact your personal warmups and pre-workouts.\r\n\r\nMoreover resistance bands will help you strengthening your body and building muscle memory. Later refers to mastering an exercise by practicing and stimulating your muscles over and over with the right range of motion locking in the correct form.\r\n\r\nRemoving “x” amount of pounds [or kg] from your own body weight, you can decrease but also increase resistance for many exercises.\r\n\r\nConsider the example of learning muscleups. To master muscleups, you must be able to perform pullups and straight bar dips. Learning a pullup is difficult and starts with a clear progression ladder as shown below. Every single time you personally struggle with an exercise in bodyweight training, you should consider using a band if possible. With the band you will gradually adjust to the strength needed and perform the exercise with improved form. Let’s have a look on how you could make use of a band learning muscleups.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Eccentric Pullups (can be done with a resistance band)</li>\r\n 	<li>Assisted Pullups (as shown in our video tutorials with a band)</li>\r\n 	<li>Pullups (Assisted Pullups are the little brother of pullups using a band)</li>\r\n 	<li>High Chest Pullups (can be done with a resistance band)</li>\r\n 	<li>Muscelups (can be done with a resistance band)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nFinally you can use resistance bands to add weight and increase resistance for certain exercises. If you are an advanced athlete, make use of your resistance bands whenever you practice different variations of push-ups, squats and dips.\r\n\r\n<strong>The most efficient tool for rapid progress in strength and making gradual improvements in technique for Ykings PBT is the resistance band. Other than that Ykings PBT is a progressive form of getting in tune with your body while you hunt down elite bodyweight skills. For each skill we have designed a clear progression ladder, so you will need to perform “A” before moving on to “B” and so on.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #f0b323;\"><strong>#StriveForProgress &amp; don’t forget #StrongIsTheNewSexy</strong></span>','Using resistance bands in bodyweight training','','inherit','closed','closed','','1765-revision-v1','','','2016-09-06 13:22:05','2016-09-06 13:22:05','',1765,'http://ykings.